00:15:50,545 --> 00:15:51,943
We can stretch out our negotiation.

508
00:15:51,944 --> 00:15:53,344
(I knew I could count on you guys.)

509
00:15:53,654 --> 00:15:56,853
(While the members are plotting against the staff...)

510
00:15:56,854 --> 00:15:58,083
(Pohang, Gyeongju)

511
00:15:58,084 --> 00:15:59,153
(the scenery changes from the ocean to the mountains.)

512
00:15:59,154 --> 00:16:00,253
We're in the mountains?

513
00:16:00,254 --> 00:16:02,414
(the scenery changes from the ocean to the mountains.)

514
00:16:03,894 --> 00:16:06,994
(Entering Gyeongju)

515
00:16:08,164 --> 00:16:10,503
(The past and present coexist in perfect harmony...)

516
00:16:10,504 --> 00:16:12,464
(in the 1,000-year-old ancient capital of Silla.)

517
00:16:13,834 --> 00:16:15,673
(A place where the rich culture of Silla...)

518
00:16:15,674 --> 00:16:19,444
(and beautiful nature are evident)

519
00:16:20,174 --> 00:16:23,914
(Today's final destination, Gyeongju)

520
00:16:24,484 --> 00:16:26,543
(However, they only have 2 minutes left...)

521
00:16:26,544 --> 00:16:28,825
(when the remaining distance to the destination is 12km.)

522
00:16:29,914 --> 00:16:32,254
We have two minutes left. Will they call us?

523
00:16:32,824 --> 00:16:34,054
Don't answer their calls.

524
00:16:34,824 --> 00:16:36,824
I'm scared.

525
00:16:38,424 --> 00:16:42,534
(They have about 10 seconds left.)

526
00:16:43,334 --> 00:16:47,174
(In about 10 seconds, )

527
00:16:47,534 --> 00:16:51,204
(they must get out of the car and walk there.)

528
00:16:53,204 --> 00:16:54,644
Wait. They're calling me.

529
00:16:56,074 --> 00:16:58,114
- My gosh.
- How do you answer a phone call?

530
00:16:58,584 --> 00:17:00,183
- You know nothing about phones.
- Right.

531
00:17:00,184 --> 00:17:01,414
- Are they calling you?
- Yes.

532
00:17:02,054 --> 00:17:03,114
DinDin.

533
00:17:04,384 --> 00:17:08,024
Yes?

534
00:17:08,454 --> 00:17:10,794
- Guys. Your time is up.
- Yes?

535
00:17:11,324 --> 00:17:12,424
Hello?

536
00:17:12,724 --> 00:17:15,864
(What a way to teach the youngest all the wrong things.)

537
00:17:15,964 --> 00:17:17,003
Hello?

538
00:17:17,004 --> 00:17:19,033
(Their walking distance is decreasing as they speak.)

539
00:17:19,034 --> 00:17:20,433
- Ask him.
- You keep breaking up.

540
00:17:20,434 --> 00:17:21,673
(The duo is doing their best to con the director.)

541
00:17:21,674 --> 00:17:24,103
It must be because we're up on the mountains.

542
00:17:24,104 --> 00:17:25,974
- The phone...
- Hello?

543
00:17:26,404 --> 00:17:27,643
You guys need to stop now.

544
00:17:27,644 --> 00:17:28,714
Get out.

545
00:17:30,344 --> 00:17:31,543
(The staff members are gathering in the drop-off point.)

546
00:17:31,544 --> 00:17:33,014
That's the place. No.

547
00:17:33,714 --> 00:17:36,114
Se Yoon, can't you just drive? It will be cool.

548
00:17:37,454 --> 00:17:38,854
(Smiling)

549
00:17:39,684 --> 00:17:40,824
I'm sorry.

550
00:17:40,954 --> 00:17:42,254
No. Come back.

551
00:17:43,524 --> 00:17:45,393
- What?
- Will they let us go?

552
00:17:45,394 --> 00:17:46,524
Will they let us go?

553
00:17:46,594 --> 00:17:48,354
- Gosh, I'm too chicken for this.
- My gosh.

554
00:17:48,964 --> 00:17:51,464
(Their car privilege is over.)

555
00:17:52,034 --> 00:17:53,833
Your time is up now.

556
00:17:53,834 --> 00:17:55,904
You'll start walking from here. Okay.

557
00:17:56,204 --> 00:17:57,274
Let's do that.

558
00:17:57,544 --> 00:17:58,873
We stalled enough time.

559
00:17:58,874 --> 00:18:00,634
(Distance remaining to the destination, 7km)

560
00:18:00,914 --> 00:18:02,113
(They have to carry their own backpack.)

561
00:18:02,114 --> 00:18:03,514
Gosh, why is it so heavy?

562
00:18:06,114 --> 00:18:09,954
(DinDin's suitcase is as big as him.)

563
00:18:10,824 --> 00:18:12,353
(They're ready to walk.)

564
00:18:12,354 --> 00:18:13,423
All right.

565
00:18:13,424 --> 00:18:15,154
It's been fun. Let's get going.

566
00:18:15,224 --> 00:18:16,254
Let's go.

567
00:18:17,824 --> 00:18:20,294
- All right. Let's get going.
- Let's go.

568
00:18:20,434 --> 00:18:23,264
You have 7km left until the base camp.

569
00:18:24,304 --> 00:18:25,333
- Great.
- Okay.

570
00:18:25,334 --> 00:18:27,473
- That must be tough.
- I can lug it like this.

571
00:18:27,474 --> 00:18:28,934
(They must walk for over 2 hours.)

572
00:18:29,034 --> 00:18:30,404
Well, it's over now.

573
00:18:31,274 --> 00:18:33,044
- We can take our time, right?
- Yes.

574
00:18:33,444 --> 00:18:34,884
Hey, you look like a drill sergeant.

575
00:18:36,014 --> 00:18:37,844
- Sergeant Lee.
- Go straight.

576
00:18:38,684 --> 00:18:42,954
Some of you still haven't learned your lesson.

577
00:18:44,024 --> 00:18:45,784
Square your shoulders.

578
00:18:46,324 --> 00:18:48,154
Lift your ribcage and march.

579
00:18:50,564 --> 00:18:52,263
Hey, that must be tough.

580
00:18:52,264 --> 00:18:53,623
(DinDin's suitcase is bothering him.)

581
00:18:53,624 --> 00:18:55,134
- Why...
- Right.

582
00:18:55,194 --> 00:18:57,734
You rarely bring a suitcase to the shoot.

583
00:18:58,564 --> 00:19:00,574
You know what? This is better than hiking.

584
00:19:01,334 --> 00:19:03,334
Remember the time when we had to hike Mount Halla.

585
00:19:03,704 --> 00:19:04,773
This is much better.

586
00:19:04,774 --> 00:19:06,143
- You didn't go with us.
- I didn't?

587
00:19:06,144 --> 00:19:08,344
(Really?)

588
00:19:08,774 --> 00:19:11,084
Trains were invented in England...

589
00:19:11,944 --> 00:19:13,584
in the early 1900s. You knew that, right?

590
00:19:14,114 --> 00:19:16,553
But now, it's been 126 years since the invention.

591
00:19:16,554 --> 00:19:17,854
Why are we still walking?

592
00:19:19,524 --> 00:19:22,553
Why? Technology has advanced so much.

593
00:19:22,554 --> 00:19:24,514
(This real variety show defies the flow of time.)

594
00:19:24,924 --> 00:19:27,764
People might think we're trying to walk across the country.

595
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:31,934
(Moon Se Yoon Walks to Gyeongju)

596
00:19:32,464 --> 00:19:34,104
On behalf of the celebrities,

597
00:19:34,634 --> 00:19:37,343
you're walking across the country. So this is your 16th day.

598
00:19:37,344 --> 00:19:39,073
- Se Yoon.
- Hello.

599
00:19:39,074 --> 00:19:40,243
You have two days left...

600
00:19:40,244 --> 00:19:41,443
- to complete the 20-day course.
- Yes.

601
00:19:41,444 --> 00:19:42,813
Where did you start?

602
00:19:42,814 --> 00:19:44,813
- I started from Donghae.
- I see.

603
00:19:44,814 --> 00:19:48,753
I began from Donghae. I've been dry-aging for 16 days.

604
00:19:48,754 --> 00:19:50,454
- I see.
- I'm gradually dry-aging.

605
00:19:50,654 --> 00:19:53,723
I'm heading toward my last destination.

606
00:19:53,724 --> 00:19:55,323
- What an impressive record.
- Right.

607
00:19:55,324 --> 00:19:58,764
You kept walking for 18 days without taking 1 day off.

608
00:19:58,894 --> 00:20:00,733
- That's right.
- You didn't even lose 1g.

609
00:20:00,734 --> 00:20:01,964
What an impressive record.

610
00:20:02,264 --> 00:20:03,634
I have the shrimp toasts to thank.

611
00:20:05,404 --> 00:20:07,004
Shrimp toasts are the best for walking.

612
00:20:08,734 --> 00:20:10,003
(Glancing back)

613
00:20:10,004 --> 00:20:12,243
The distance is widening. He has a suitcase.

614
00:20:12,244 --> 00:20:13,773
(The distance between the two groups is widening more.)

615
00:20:13,774 --> 00:20:14,914
I guess it's hard to lug it.

616
00:20:16,174 --> 00:20:19,244
(The suitcase is the obstacle as expected.)

617
00:20:20,554 --> 00:20:21,583
My gosh.

618
00:20:21,584 --> 00:20:22,753
- What is it? Are you okay?
- Are you okay?

619
00:20:22,754 --> 00:20:23,784
Yes.

620
00:20:24,354 --> 00:20:26,424
(Getting furious)

621
00:20:26,554 --> 00:20:27,794
- You're not hurt?
- No.

622
00:20:29,254 --> 00:20:30,294
Come on.

623
00:20:31,664 --> 00:20:32,863
This is so frustrating.

624
00:20:32,864 --> 00:20:34,540
(Smiling through frustration makes you top-tier.)

625
00:20:34,564 --> 00:20:36,063
I feel like I'm traveling in Europe.

626
00:20:36,064 --> 00:20:38,334
(I feel like I'm traveling in Europe.)

627
00:20:39,304 --> 00:20:40,804
- Realistically speaking, - Yes.

628
00:20:41,334 --> 00:20:44,544
It was impossible to get there by 6pm.

629
00:20:44,704 --> 00:20:47,844
Are they trying to make us do the impossible?

630
00:20:48,514 --> 00:20:50,413
We were bound to walk.

631
00:20:50,414 --> 00:20:52,090
(It's been 40 minutes since they've been walking.)

632
00:20:52,114 --> 00:20:54,283
The backpack is quite heavy.

633
00:20:54,284 --> 00:20:55,554
It's getting heavier.

634
00:20:56,614 --> 00:20:58,883
My gosh. We're in Gyeongju?

635
00:20:58,884 --> 00:21:00,724
- What?
- We're in Gyeongju?

636
00:21:00,994 --> 00:21:02,023
We're in Gyeongju.

637
00:21:02,024 --> 00:21:03,093
(Carrying their heavy bags...)

638
00:21:03,094 --> 00:21:09,264
(slows them down little by little.)

639
00:21:10,164 --> 00:21:15,573
(Everyone stops talking.)

640
00:21:15,574 --> 00:21:17,304
How long did we walk? About 3km?

641
00:21:17,474 --> 00:21:18,944
I think we walked about 2.5km.

642
00:21:20,004 --> 00:21:21,244
I don't think it's been 1km.

643
00:21:21,444 --> 00:21:22,913
We walked for about 1km.

644
00:21:22,914 --> 00:21:24,144
- It must be over 1km.
- Yes.

645
00:21:24,684 --> 00:21:25,783
Are you okay?

646
00:21:25,784 --> 00:21:28,484
(They haven't even made halfway yet after 40 minutes of walking.)

647
00:21:28,754 --> 00:21:30,184
My suitcase is making a sound.

648
00:21:30,454 --> 00:21:33,154
- Really?
- His suitcase is crying.

649
00:21:33,924 --> 00:21:35,353
The suitcase is crying.

650
00:21:35,354 --> 00:21:37,294
- It's begging to be thrown out.
- All right.

651
00:21:37,624 --> 00:21:38,693
- Guys.
- Help us.

652
00:21:38,694 --> 00:21:40,124
- Where are we going?
- Hold on.

653
00:21:40,564 --> 00:21:42,333
- There's a car.
- What?

654
00:21:42,334 --> 00:21:43,593
(A car is approaching them.)

655
00:21:43,594 --> 00:21:45,504
Hey. I think they're going to rescue one of us.

656
00:21:45,704 --> 00:21:47,134
- Guys.
- What?

657
00:21:47,304 --> 00:21:48,973
You can just take my bag. That's all I need.

658
00:21:48,974 --> 00:21:50,973
All of you guys worked very hard.

659
00:21:50,974 --> 00:21:52,004
- Okay.
- We'll rescue...

660
00:21:52,344 --> 00:21:53,914
Okay. How many?

661
00:21:54,774 --> 00:21:56,113
- two of you.
- Okay.

662
00:21:56,114 --> 00:21:57,390
- We'll give them a ride.
- Two?

663
00:21:57,414 --> 00:21:59,144
- I see.
- Two?

664
00:21:59,684 --> 00:22:00,954
That's the deal.

665
00:22:01,354 --> 00:22:03,713
Last time, we played Check in, One, Two, Three.

666
00:22:03,714 --> 00:22:04,783
- Yes.
- We had to crouch down or get up.

667
00:22:04,784 --> 00:22:06,830
The only one crouching down or standing up will win.

668
00:22:06,854 --> 00:22:07,924
Okay.

669
00:22:08,054 --> 00:22:09,853
- Just one. We'll play it twice.
- One each?

670
00:22:09,854 --> 00:22:10,893
- Okay.
- Okay.

671
00:22:10,894 --> 00:22:12,323
Until only one of us does a different action?

672
00:22:12,324 --> 00:22:13,424
- Yes.
- Yes.

673
00:22:13,934 --> 00:22:15,893
(Which two members will be rescued from this difficult march?)

674
00:22:15,894 --> 00:22:16,964
Let's begin.

675
00:22:18,564 --> 00:22:19,834
One, two, three.

676
00:22:21,804 --> 00:22:23,033
(Se Yoon and Yong Jin get up.)

677
00:22:23,034 --> 00:22:24,303
He got up.

678
00:22:24,304 --> 00:22:26,304
- Nice save.
- Okay.

679
00:22:26,704 --> 00:22:27,773
- Okay.
- Nice save.

680
00:22:27,774 --> 00:22:29,513
- I got up. You saw that, right?
- Nice save.

681
00:22:29,514 --> 00:22:31,114
- Let's begin.
- He's sweating so much.

682
00:22:31,414 --> 00:22:32,483
Give him chili japchae.

683
00:22:32,484 --> 00:22:34,853
- Give me the japchae now.
- The japchae.

684
00:22:34,854 --> 00:22:36,334
- He must eat japchae.
- Let's begin.

685
00:22:37,284 --> 00:22:38,584
One, two, three.

686
00:22:40,224 --> 00:22:41,494
(Disappointed)

687
00:22:41,824 --> 00:22:43,094
- Here it goes.
- Okay.

688
00:22:43,294 --> 00:22:44,594
One, two, three.

689
00:22:44,694 --> 00:22:45,764
- All right.
- Okay.

690
00:22:47,964 --> 00:22:48,964
Here it goes.

691
00:22:49,964 --> 00:22:51,063
One, two, three.

692
00:22:51,064 --> 00:22:52,064
There.

693
00:22:52,065 --> 00:22:53,233
- Okay!
- Gosh.

694
00:22:53,234 --> 00:22:54,234
There.

695
00:22:54,235 --> 00:22:55,803
(Joon is rescued.)

696
00:22:55,804 --> 00:22:57,134
- Darn it.
- Joon.

697
00:22:57,774 --> 00:22:58,844
- Darn it.
- Joon.

698
00:22:59,474 --> 00:23:01,113
- All right.
- The last one.

699
00:23:01,114 --> 00:23:02,614
There's only one more spot left.

700
00:23:03,314 --> 00:23:05,843
I need to be smart about this. Will they squat down or get up?

701
00:23:05,844 --> 00:23:07,183
- Okay.
- He and Ki Taek...

702
00:23:07,184 --> 00:23:08,353
- Hey.
- We'll squat down.

703
00:23:08,354 --> 00:23:10,453
- Okay. What will you do then?
- You do whatever you want.

704
00:23:10,454 --> 00:23:12,484
- Men ought to stand up.
- What about you?

705
00:23:12,784 --> 00:23:13,923
I'll stand up too.

706
00:23:13,924 --> 00:23:15,053
(He'll stand up.)

707
00:23:15,054 --> 00:23:16,324
- I'll squat down.
- Okay.

708
00:23:17,194 --> 00:23:18,194
- This is pointless.
- Here it goes.

709
00:23:18,195 --> 00:23:19,264
We're going to squat down.

710
00:23:20,024 --> 00:23:21,364
One, two, three.

711
00:23:22,537 --> 00:23:23,537
One, two, three.

712
00:23:25,091 --> 00:23:26,501
I told you I would squat down.

713
00:23:27,031 --> 00:23:28,537
- Hey, why didn't you squat down?
- I told you.

714
00:23:28,561 --> 00:23:30,070
- Didn't I squat down?
- Why didn't you squat down?

715
00:23:30,071 --> 00:23:31,071
I wanted you to...

716
00:23:31,271 --> 00:23:32,970
(I, Lee Yong Jin, keep my word.)

717
00:23:32,971 --> 00:23:34,540
- Can you include one more person?
- No.

718
00:23:34,541 --> 00:23:35,601
- Okay.
- Let's go.

719
00:23:35,841 --> 00:23:37,271
- You've become so ruthless.
- Yes.

720
00:23:38,141 --> 00:23:39,141
He's changed.

721
00:23:39,142 --> 00:23:40,711
He's more like Min So Hee today.

722
00:23:41,241 --> 00:23:42,241
All right.

723
00:23:45,581 --> 00:23:47,421
- We'll get going.
- Bye.

724
00:23:47,981 --> 00:23:50,491
(Goodbye, Yong Jin.)

725
00:23:51,351 --> 00:23:52,351
Go.

726
00:23:52,721 --> 00:23:53,721
Goodbye.

727
00:23:54,021 --> 00:23:55,320
- They're leaving.
- They're leaving right away.

728
00:23:55,321 --> 00:23:57,161
(The van drives off without a second thought.)

729
00:23:57,891 --> 00:23:59,131
Look at the clouds.

730
00:23:59,501 --> 00:24:01,261
- It'd be difficult with the rain.
- I know.

731
00:24:01,901 --> 00:24:03,131
We're so lucky.

732
00:24:04,331 --> 00:24:06,401
- It takes a long time to get there.
- Exactly.

733
00:24:06,801 --> 00:24:08,970
When you get a chance like this on the show, you must take it.

734
00:24:08,971 --> 00:24:11,371
- Definitely.
- It's merciless.

735
00:24:11,841 --> 00:24:14,140
- You sleep indoors when you can.
- Of course.

736
00:24:14,141 --> 00:24:15,981
When they give you a chance to eat, you eat.

737
00:24:16,041 --> 00:24:17,081
I completely agree.

738
00:24:17,951 --> 00:24:20,450
- This is way too far.
- It's really far.

739
00:24:20,451 --> 00:24:21,851
(They've been driving for a while.)

740
00:24:22,081 --> 00:24:24,161
We can get some rest before everyone else gets here.

741
00:24:25,121 --> 00:24:26,891
Let's get there soon and recharge.

742
00:24:27,021 --> 00:24:29,531
We need to keep our strength and play Dinner Game.

743
00:24:29,891 --> 00:24:31,191
And pick where we sleep tonight.

744
00:24:31,961 --> 00:24:33,800
This is too far to get here on foot.

745
00:24:33,801 --> 00:24:36,430
(The drive continues for a long time.)

746
00:24:36,431 --> 00:24:37,470
Is this it?

747
00:24:37,471 --> 00:24:38,600
(Yong Jin and Joon arrive at the base camp.)

748
00:24:38,601 --> 00:24:39,701
So this is the base camp.

749
00:24:40,641 --> 00:24:41,671
It's nice.

750
00:24:41,971 --> 00:24:43,511
It's really nice.

751
00:24:43,871 --> 00:24:45,741
With an accommodation of this size,

752
00:24:46,441 --> 00:24:49,451
- some will sleep indoors tonight.
- Definitely.

753
00:24:50,981 --> 00:24:53,150
- Let's get some rest.
- To win...

754
00:24:53,151 --> 00:24:55,197
(The two of them are finally free from their luggage.)

755
00:24:55,221 --> 00:24:58,321
(Flopping down immediately)

756
00:24:58,721 --> 00:25:01,421
(The first moment of lying down during this trip)

757
00:25:02,491 --> 00:25:04,230
- We're in paradise.
- Yes.

758
00:25:04,231 --> 00:25:05,891
(Now this is paradise.)

759
00:25:06,301 --> 00:25:08,181
- How long does it take from here?
- From here?

760
00:25:08,561 --> 00:25:09,771
About 40 to 50 minutes.

761
00:25:10,171 --> 00:25:11,400
The sun is going down.

762
00:25:11,401 --> 00:25:12,500
(Let's hurry and walk before the sun goes down.)

763
00:25:12,501 --> 00:25:14,801
