Still?

1025
00:33:48,781 --> 00:33:49,821
(Inhaling bitterly)

1026
00:33:50,651 --> 00:33:52,951
(Getting tired)

1027
00:33:53,021 --> 00:33:54,961
But we're halfway there, right?

1028
00:33:56,021 --> 00:33:57,060
(Laughing instead of responding)

1029
00:33:57,061 --> 00:33:58,061
I guess not.

1030
00:33:58,791 --> 00:33:59,861
We're not.

1031
00:34:00,461 --> 00:34:03,601
(They barely advanced 1km.)

1032
00:34:04,731 --> 00:34:06,971
- It's raining.
- It's raining harder.

1033
00:34:08,341 --> 00:34:10,511
Gosh, the timing is perfect.

1034
00:34:11,341 --> 00:34:12,840
It's pouring.

1035
00:34:12,841 --> 00:34:13,880
It's a shower.

1036
00:34:13,881 --> 00:34:15,341
(Trudging through the pouring rain)

1037
00:34:17,281 --> 00:34:18,611
Don't people call this charming?

1038
00:34:18,681 --> 00:34:20,420
What do you think, DinDin? It's raining heavily now.

1039
00:34:20,421 --> 00:34:22,150
- I like when it rains.
- Really?

1040
00:34:22,151 --> 00:34:24,690
I don't mind walking in the rain,

1041
00:34:24,691 --> 00:34:26,760
- but do you see the insects here?
- Yes.

1042
00:34:26,761 --> 00:34:28,921
These are making me very angry.

1043
00:34:31,331 --> 00:34:32,331
Look over there.

1044
00:34:32,861 --> 00:34:35,300
- All the insects are gathered.
- Right.

1045
00:34:35,301 --> 00:34:37,931
(Walking alongside a swarm of flying insects)

1046
00:34:38,401 --> 00:34:40,471
(A popular spot for flying insects)

1047
00:34:40,771 --> 00:34:43,170
(Aggressive country flying bugs)

1048
00:34:43,171 --> 00:34:45,670
We're halfway there, aren't we?

1049
00:34:45,671 --> 00:34:46,671
(Asking for the third time)

1050
00:34:46,672 --> 00:34:47,740
(Once again, silence is their response.)

1051
00:34:47,741 --> 00:34:48,811
I see.

1052
00:34:49,741 --> 00:34:51,381
Did you ever regret joining the show?

1053
00:34:51,911 --> 00:34:53,550
- You mean, choosing 2 Days 1 Night?
- Yes.

1054
00:34:53,551 --> 00:34:54,621
No, I never did.

1055
00:34:54,751 --> 00:34:56,521
I ask because it's exhausting.

1056
00:34:57,021 --> 00:34:59,890
It's especially hard when it overlaps...

1057
00:34:59,891 --> 00:35:00,891
with your other projects.

1058
00:35:00,892 --> 00:35:02,761
That's what's happening now.

1059
00:35:02,961 --> 00:35:05,760
It's tough, but once the shoot ends, I always think it was fun.

1060
00:35:05,761 --> 00:35:07,030
- Really?
- That's why...

1061
00:35:07,031 --> 00:35:08,200
After the shoot?

1062
00:35:08,201 --> 00:35:09,300
After the shoot.

1063
00:35:09,301 --> 00:35:11,330
During the shoot, you don't enjoy it, do you?

1064
00:35:11,331 --> 00:35:12,831
It's still fun.

1065
00:35:13,371 --> 00:35:15,640
When the shoot ends, I find myself wanting to come back.

1066
00:35:15,641 --> 00:35:17,010
- I see.
- Isn't it the same for you?

1067
00:35:17,011 --> 00:35:18,340
- What do you think?
- For me,

1068
00:35:18,341 --> 00:35:20,611
I want a break for one month.

1069
00:35:22,611 --> 00:35:23,950
I'd like a one-month break.

1070
00:35:23,951 --> 00:35:24,951
(Seeing family is good in small doses.)

1071
00:35:24,952 --> 00:35:26,150
(Meanwhile, heavy rain pours down at the base camp.)

1072
00:35:26,151 --> 00:35:27,251
What?

1073
00:35:27,281 --> 00:35:29,151
- Get up.
- Get up.

1074
00:35:29,321 --> 00:35:31,751
- What happened?
- You know how we survived?

1075
00:35:32,521 --> 00:35:33,620
We survived a total nightmare.

1076
00:35:33,621 --> 00:35:35,120
- After you guys left...
- How...

1077
00:35:35,121 --> 00:35:36,221
How did you do it?

1078
00:35:36,521 --> 00:35:38,491
- It's embarrassing to say.
- What did you win?

1079
00:35:38,531 --> 00:35:39,531
Rock-paper-scissors.

1080
00:35:39,532 --> 00:35:40,907
- That's what Se Yoon won.
- Really?

1081
00:35:40,931 --> 00:35:43,000
- Gosh.
- He played scissors and won.

1082
00:35:43,001 --> 00:35:45,200
Isn't it very dark outside?

1083
00:35:45,201 --> 00:35:46,840
- It's dark.
- It's very dark.

1084
00:35:46,841 --> 00:35:48,401
Water deer are roaming outside too.

1085
00:35:48,941 --> 00:35:51,470
The youngest ones are walking.

1086
00:35:51,471 --> 00:35:53,441
- Right.
- That's at least something.

1087
00:35:53,711 --> 00:35:55,157
Now that I think about it, you're right.

1088
00:35:55,181 --> 00:35:56,181
(The eldest is out of it.)

1089
00:35:56,182 --> 00:35:58,880
- Today has been exhausting.
- I agree.

1090
00:35:58,881 --> 00:36:00,010
(It's been exhausting for the older ones.)

1091
00:36:00,011 --> 00:36:01,121
My eyes are closing.

1092
00:36:01,321 --> 00:36:02,321
The day is long.

1093
00:36:04,321 --> 00:36:06,891
(Sleep starts to creep in.)

1094
00:36:07,161 --> 00:36:08,661
Se Yoon, it's raining so hard.

1095
00:36:09,061 --> 00:36:10,790
- Are they going to be okay?
- Is it raining hard?

1096
00:36:10,791 --> 00:36:11,791
- It's raining hard.
- Seriously.

1097
00:36:11,791 --> 00:36:12,791
Yes, it's pouring.

1098
00:36:12,831 --> 00:36:14,031
All we can do is pray.

1099
00:36:14,661 --> 00:36:15,731
(Praying)

1100
00:36:17,171 --> 00:36:19,571
That's the confidence of a survivor.

1101
00:36:20,171 --> 00:36:21,171
You're so relaxed.

1102
00:36:21,201 --> 00:36:22,240
That's funny.

1103
00:36:22,241 --> 00:36:23,870
- We're relaxed.
- At least there are two of them.

1104
00:36:23,871 --> 00:36:25,070
- We're relaxed.
- Right?

1105
00:36:25,071 --> 00:36:26,140
(The living have to keep living.)

1106
00:36:26,141 --> 00:36:27,180
(Current location)

1107
00:36:27,181 --> 00:36:29,681
(Walking for 1 hour and 40 minutes)

1108
00:36:29,881 --> 00:36:32,051
(Nothing but darkness in sight)

1109
00:36:32,651 --> 00:36:33,651
(Splashing)

1110
00:36:34,251 --> 00:36:35,281
It's raining hard.

1111
00:36:35,751 --> 00:36:36,751
(Suddenly, the camera crew gets busy.)

1112
00:36:36,752 --> 00:36:37,791
It's raining hard.

1113
00:36:39,121 --> 00:36:40,360
It's raining really hard.

1114
00:36:40,361 --> 00:36:41,921
(The rain suddenly comes pouring down.)

1115
00:36:42,761 --> 00:36:45,491
(Drenched)

1116
00:36:45,731 --> 00:36:47,531
We have to be close by now.

1117
00:36:47,731 --> 00:36:49,330
This GoPro camera went out.

1118
00:36:49,331 --> 00:36:51,501
(Even the camera goes out.)

1119
00:36:52,601 --> 00:36:54,721
(Spotting the headlights after 1 hour and 40 minutes)

1120
00:36:55,171 --> 00:36:56,171
Is that our car?

1121
00:36:56,172 --> 00:36:58,140
(No)

1122
00:36:58,141 --> 00:36:59,211
I wish it were our car.

1123
00:37:00,781 --> 00:37:03,510
- Help!
- Please give us a ride.

1124
00:37:03,511 --> 00:37:05,950
- Help us.
- Give us a ride.

1125
00:37:05,951 --> 00:37:07,821
(Please come rescue us.)

1126
00:37:08,021 --> 00:37:09,981
- We've walked a lot.
- There's a frog.

1127
00:37:10,051 --> 00:37:11,051
A frog?

1128
00:37:11,221 --> 00:37:12,420
It's really a frog.

1129
00:37:12,421 --> 00:37:13,450
(They're happy to see a frog even in their misery.)

1130
00:37:13,451 --> 00:37:15,221
I feel like I'm back in the military.

1131
00:37:15,421 --> 00:37:16,690
(It feels like we're stuck in a nightmare.)

1132
00:37:16,691 --> 00:37:17,731
A frog...

1133
00:37:18,891 --> 00:37:21,560
We're almost there, aren't we?

1134
00:37:21,561 --> 00:37:22,961
(Asking for the eighth time)

1135
00:37:23,531 --> 00:37:24,531
That must be it.

1136
00:37:24,532 --> 00:37:25,830
(A light appears in the distance.)

1137
00:37:25,831 --> 00:37:27,001
Isn't that it?

1138
00:37:27,771 --> 00:37:28,851
Let's move the base camp...

1139
00:37:29,341 --> 00:37:30,341
to there.

1140
00:37:31,541 --> 00:37:32,711
I'm hungry.

1141
00:37:32,911 --> 00:37:34,140
I don't usually eat much.

1142
00:37:34,141 --> 00:37:35,240
(Hunger suddenly hits.)

1143
00:37:35,241 --> 00:37:36,310
I digest food really fast.

1144
00:37:36,311 --> 00:37:37,391
Do you want some dumplings?

1145
00:37:37,811 --> 00:37:39,511
Dumplings? I had a lot earlier.

1146
00:37:39,951 --> 00:37:40,981
I'm tired of dumplings.

1147
00:37:41,821 --> 00:37:44,090
I want something like stir-fried spicy pork.

1148
00:37:44,091 --> 00:37:45,571
Cheonggukjang, stir-fried spicy pork,

1149
00:37:45,891 --> 00:37:46,920
backbone hangover soup.

1150
00:37:46,921 --> 00:37:48,921
(Ki Taek's choice of night snack)

1151
00:37:49,221 --> 00:37:51,960
(When things get rough, all you can think about is good food.)

1152
00:37:51,961 --> 00:37:52,961
(Base camp, current location)

1153
00:37:52,962 --> 00:37:55,160
We made it into the village.

1154
00:37:55,161 --> 00:37:56,601
I think I can see the base camp.

1155
00:37:57,871 --> 00:37:59,171
"Rural Experience Village."

1156
00:38:00,371 --> 00:38:01,841
I see it now.

1157
00:38:03,041 --> 00:38:05,271
We came all the way here from Donghae.

1158
00:38:06,841 --> 00:38:09,740
(They finally enter the base camp.)

1159
00:38:09,741 --> 00:38:10,781
We're here.

1160
00:38:11,851 --> 00:38:14,351
(They arrived after walking for 2 hours and 30 minutes.)

1161
00:38:15,351 --> 00:38:16,880
You arrived safely...

1162
00:38:16,881 --> 00:38:19,520
at the Gyeongju base camp on Route Seven.

1163
00:38:19,521 --> 00:38:21,790
Please head to the rest-up room.

1164
00:38:21,791 --> 00:38:22,860
- The rest-up room?
- Yes.

1165
00:38:22,861 --> 00:38:24,341
(They head to enjoy some sweet rest.)

1166
00:38:24,591 --> 00:38:26,560
Okay. My shoulders...

1167
00:38:26,561 --> 00:38:28,331
They could've put this inside.

1168
00:38:29,261 --> 00:38:30,901
I feel like my shoulders will fall off.

1169
00:38:31,801 --> 00:38:37,511
(They have no energy left to walk to the room.)

1170
00:38:37,611 --> 00:38:39,711
Well done, everyone.

1171
00:38:40,381 --> 00:38:41,381
Well done.

1172
00:38:41,441 --> 00:38:44,311
(Bedraggled)

1173
00:38:46,181 --> 00:38:48,350
- We're here.
- You must be completely wet.

1174
00:38:48,351 --> 00:38:49,780
- I'm wet.
- Goodness.

1175
00:38:49,781 --> 00:38:51,490
(The older members welcome him.)

1176
00:38:51,491 --> 00:38:53,491
- That must've been tough.
- It was really hard.

1177
00:38:54,491 --> 00:38:56,460
- Are you okay?
- You're completely soaked.

1178
00:38:56,461 --> 00:38:57,760
- Goodness.
- My shoulders are...

1179
00:38:57,761 --> 00:38:59,067
- about to fall off.
- Let me see.

1180
00:38:59,091 --> 00:39:00,730
- Where's DinDin?
- Hey, DinDin.

1181
00:39:00,731 --> 00:39:02,000
(Drenched Mouse DinDin also comes in.)

1182
00:39:02,001 --> 00:39:03,261
- Good job.
- My shoulders...

1183
00:39:03,871 --> 00:39:05,830
- Are you okay?
- It was pouring outside.

1184
00:39:05,831 --> 00:39:07,670
You're completely wet.

1185
00:39:07,671 --> 00:39:09,500
- The rain poured.
- Seriously.

1186
00:39:09,501 --> 00:39:10,540
(The older guys can't help but feel bad for the younger ones.)

1187
00:39:10,541 --> 00:39:11,940
Well done, guys.

1188
00:39:11,941 --> 00:39:13,941
Shouldn't they get some rest?

1189
00:39:14,141 --> 00:39:15,910
- Get some rest.
- More importantly,

1190
00:39:15,911 --> 00:39:18,410
they came back all sour.

1191
00:39:18,411 --> 00:39:20,150
- A moment ago...
- They have gone sour.

1192
00:39:20,151 --> 00:39:22,050
It must've been like shooting a coming-of-age drama.

1193
00:39:22,051 --> 00:39:23,750
(A coming-of-age drama that's gone sour)

1194
00:39:23,751 --> 00:39:25,290
Our boys went through so much. What are you going to do?

1195
00:39:25,291 --> 00:39:26,851
- Everyone.
- How will you remedy this?

1196
00:39:27,091 --> 00:39:29,290
- You went through a lot today.
- They're all wet.

1197
00:39:29,291 --> 00:39:31,630
Did those who took a break get some rest?

1198
00:39:31,631 --> 00:39:34,061
- Not really.
- Next, we'll proceed...

1199
00:39:34,701 --> 00:39:36,200
to Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors.

1200
00:39:36,201 --> 00:39:37,771
- Right away?
- Immediately?

1201
00:39:38,501 --> 00:39:39,730
Doing it right away is better.

1202
00:39:39,731 --> 00:39:41,600
- Has the rain stopped?
- Do you have strength left?

1203
00:39:41,601 --> 00:39:43,740
- It's still raining?
- Do you have strength left?

1204
00:39:43,741 --> 00:39:45,870
When did I ever consider my strength while shooting 2 Days 1 Night?

1205
00:39:45,871 --> 00:39:47,180
What's gotten into you?

1206
00:39:47,181 --> 00:39:49,140
I don't care even if I pass out.

1207
00:39:49,141 --> 00:39:50,510
- He's back with a better mindset.
- That's amazing.

1208
00:39:50,511 --> 00:39:52,350
- Maybe a struggle is good for you.
- No.

1209
00:39:52,351 --> 00:39:56,280
I walked 22,000 steps today.

1210
00:39:56,281 --> 00:39:57,350
You know what?

1211
00:39:57,351 --> 00:39:59,150
Your life probably increased because you're healthier now.

1212
00:39:59,151 --> 00:40:01,321
- No, I'll pass out tomorrow.
- You mean "lifespan."

1213
00:40:01,461 --> 00:40:03,790
All right, everyone.

1214
00:40:03,791 --> 00:40:05,760
- How about a ten-minute break?
- Okay.

1215
00:40:05,761 --> 00:40:07,201
Well done, guys.

1216
00:40:07,361 --> 00:40:08,860
You went through a lot.

1217
00:40:08,861 --> 00:40:09,900
(A sweet break for DinDin and Ki Taek who walked all the way)

1218
00:40:09,901 --> 00:40:11,171
(Grunting)

1219
00:40:12,171 --> 00:40:13,171
(Groaning)

1220
00:40:13,172 --> 00:40:15,571
(A groan comes out naturally.)

1221
00:40:17,001 --> 00:40:20,341
(I want to go home.)

1222
00:40:21,011 --> 00:40:23,380
(A sweet 10-minute break is over in no time.)

1223
00:40:23,381 --> 00:40:24,510
It's raining.

1224
00:40:24,511 --> 00:40:25,810
It's raining quite a lot.

1225
00:40:25,811 --> 00:40:26,910
- Right.
- Yes.

1226
00:40:26,911 --> 00:40:27,920
(Sleeping Indoors and Outdoors on a rainy night)

1227
00:40:27,921 --> 00:40:28,921
It's raining.

1228
00:40:28,922 --> 00:40:30,321
This feels romantic.

1229
00:40:30,891 --> 00:40:33,090
You probably got to see it now that it's late at night.

1230
00:40:33,091 --> 00:40:34,891
- Yes.
- Today's base camp is...

1231
00:40:35,191 --> 00:40:37,161
a renovated school that's been closed down.

1232
00:40:37,331 --> 00:40:38,391
That's nice.

1233
00:40:39,131 --> 00:40:42,761
(Like going back to our childhood days)

1234
00:40:43,601 --> 00:40:45,530
Running around this huge playground will...

1235
00:40:45,531 --> 00:40:47,671
bring back the spirit of a real variety show.

1236
00:40:48,501 --> 00:40:50,261
Tonight's Sleeping Indoors or Outdoors is...

1237
00:40:50,441 --> 00:40:52,011
sleeping ability test.

1238
00:40:52,941 --> 00:40:54,041
"Sleeping ability?"

1239
00:40:55,141 --> 00:40:57,311
It's a 3-on-3 team match,

1240
00:40:57,351 --> 00:40:59,111
and it's best of three.

1241
00:40:59,451 --> 00:41:00,851
The winning team...

1242
00:41:01,151 --> 00:41:02,420
will sleep indoors.

1243
00:41:02,421 --> 00:41:04,420
- That's a given.
- Of course.

1244
00:41:04,421 --> 00:41:06,101
- Since it's raining.
- The losing team...

1245
00:41:06,291 --> 00:41:07,461
Do you see that?

1246
00:41:09,661 --> 00:41:11,790
The losing team will sleep outside...

1247
00:41:11,791 --> 00:41:13,130
at the pavilion on the playground.

1248
00:41:13,131 --> 00:41:15,831
(Penalty for the losing team)

1249
00:41:16,701 --> 00:41:22,041
(Do you like to sleep outdoors on a rainy day?)

1250
00:41:22,441 --> 00:41:23,747
Are we sleeping outdoors without anything?

1251
00:41:23,771 --> 00:41:25,141
What about a tent?

1252
00:41:25,671 --> 00:41:26,741
You get a mosquito net.

1253
00:41:27,811 --> 00:41:29,040
(You'll be cozy with your mosquito net.)

1254
00:41:29,041 --> 00:41:31,151
(It means sleeping outdoors without anything.)

1255
00:41:31,251 --> 00:41:32,451
But it's raining.

1256
00:41:32,851 --> 00:41:33,950
There's still a roof.

1257
00:41:33,951 --> 00:41:37,650
This can't become the default. I'm serious.

1258
00:41:37,651 --> 00:41:39,890
It's still early on,

1259
00:41:39,891 --> 00:41:41,760
so it's good to show the new members...

1260
00:41:41,761 --> 00:41:43,391
what 2 Days 1 Night is all about.

1261
00:41:43,661 --> 00:41:45,260
But the symbolic meaning...

1262
00:41:45,261 --> 00:41:46,891
of sleeping outdoors has disappeared.

1263
00:41:46,961 --> 00:41:48,561
I can't let this slide.

1264
00:41:49,131 --> 00:41:50,971
What do you think, Jong Min? In this weather,

1265
00:41:51,031 --> 00:41:52,430
can you sleep outdoors with a mosquito tent?

1266
00:41:52,431 --> 00:41:54,271
- That sounds refreshing.
- I agree with him.

1267
00:41:54,841 --> 00:41:56,870
(This isn't what I was hoping for.)

1268
00:41:56,871 --> 00:41:57,871
What about you, Yong Jin?

1269
00:41:57,872 --> 00:42:00,310
Sleeping outdoors. I love it.

1270
00:42:00,311 --> 00:42:01,610
- Three consecutive times.
- Sleeping outdoors.

1271
00:42:01,611 --> 00:42:02,911
Yes, sleeping outdoors.

1272
00:42:03,141 --> 00:42:05,511
(Everyone seems okay with it.)

1273
00:42:06,011 --> 00:42:07,620
(His pouting level is rising.)

1274
00:42:07,621 --> 00:42:10,320
Please come back.

1275
00:42:10,321 --> 00:42:12,097
(Let's play the game instead of wasting time.)

1276
00:42:12,121 --> 00:42:13,227
What shall we pick our teams?

1277
00:42:13,251 --> 00:42:17,060
You're free to choose your teammates.

1278
00:42:17,061 --> 00:42:19,690
Ki Taek and DinDin should get to know each other.

1279
00:42:19,691 --> 00:42:22,330
Would you like to team up or split?

1280
00:42:22,331 --> 00:42:23,331
What do you think?

1281
