This is what Ki Taek and I talked about on our way here.

1284
00:42:29,941 --> 00:42:32,170
We realized that he's lost every game.

1285
00:42:32,171 --> 00:42:33,570
So I said...

1286
00:42:33,571 --> 00:42:36,811
that he wasn't good at anything.

1287
00:42:37,041 --> 00:42:39,481
You don't have anything you're exceptionally good at.

1288
00:42:40,051 --> 00:42:42,050
I'm disappointed by you.

1289
00:42:42,051 --> 00:42:43,080
(Ki Taek, I'm a little disappointed by you.)

1290
00:42:43,081 --> 00:42:44,921
I'm lucky when it comes to teams.

1291
00:42:45,391 --> 00:42:47,291
I'm lucky when it comes to teams.

1292
00:42:48,591 --> 00:42:50,390
- This is what he said.
- I'm lucky when it comes to teams.

1293
00:42:50,391 --> 00:42:51,960
He's lucky when it comes to teams.

1294
00:42:51,961 --> 00:42:54,801
It'd be good to split and see what happens.

1295
00:42:55,631 --> 00:42:57,431
Let's divide into Team Tall and Team Short.

1296
00:42:57,531 --> 00:43:00,031
- Team Tall, Team Short.
- Team Tall versus Team Short.

1297
00:43:00,131 --> 00:43:02,370
- Cheol and I...
- You'll play rock-paper-scissors.

1298
00:43:02,371 --> 00:43:04,040
We'll divide into Team Tall and Team Short.

1299
00:43:04,041 --> 00:43:05,041
- What do you think?
- And you pick the teammates?

1300
00:43:05,042 --> 00:43:06,610
- Yes.
- Okay.

1301
00:43:06,611 --> 00:43:07,680
Rock-paper-scissors.

1302
00:43:07,681 --> 00:43:08,780
Then you should...

1303
00:43:08,781 --> 00:43:10,341
(DinDin wins.)

1304
00:43:10,441 --> 00:43:12,211
- I'll pick Yong Jin.
- Yes.

1305
00:43:12,481 --> 00:43:14,151
He has good judgment.

1306
00:43:14,281 --> 00:43:15,980
It's tormenting to have him on the opposing team.

1307
00:43:15,981 --> 00:43:17,120
- Instead of having him...
- That team is strong.

1308
00:43:17,121 --> 00:43:18,690
As an opponent,

1309
00:43:18,691 --> 00:43:19,790
I wanted him on my team.

1310
00:43:19,791 --> 00:43:21,690
- That team is already strong.
- It's way too strong.

1311
00:43:21,691 --> 00:43:22,790
Next is...

1312
00:43:22,791 --> 00:43:24,360
- Ki Taek.
- I'll pick Se Yoon.

1313
00:43:24,361 --> 00:43:26,290
- Ki Taek.
- What's the reason?

1314
00:43:26,291 --> 00:43:28,161
I need strength that's guaranteed.

1315
00:43:28,361 --> 00:43:29,501
All right.

1316
00:43:29,701 --> 00:43:31,600
- Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors.
- Rock-paper-scissors.

1317
00:43:31,601 --> 00:43:33,001
(Ki Taek wins.)

1318
00:43:33,701 --> 00:43:34,840
I choose Joon.

1319
00:43:34,841 --> 00:43:36,270
(Shouting)

1320
00:43:36,271 --> 00:43:37,840
I choose Joon.

1321
00:43:37,841 --> 00:43:39,040
Why? What about him?

1322
00:43:39,041 --> 00:43:40,070
- I'm sorry.
- Why?

1323
00:43:40,071 --> 00:43:41,140
I'm sorry.

1324
00:43:41,141 --> 00:43:43,440
(Joon, why are you so upset?)

1325
00:43:43,441 --> 00:43:45,810
- What... Why...
- Ki Taek, I'm sorry. Hold on.

1326
00:43:45,811 --> 00:43:47,451
It just slipped out.

1327
00:43:47,981 --> 00:43:49,450
- I'm sorry, Ki Taek.
- Why did you do that?

1328
00:43:49,451 --> 00:43:51,150
Hold on. I'm so sorry. I...

1329
00:43:51,151 --> 00:43:52,950
(He's currently the weakest link in games.)

1330
00:43:52,951 --> 00:43:54,390
- Let's begin.
- Let's do this.

1331
00:43:54,391 --> 00:43:56,020
- We can do this.
- Let's go for it.

1332
00:43:56,021 --> 00:43:57,060
- I hope it's not a physical game.
- I'm confident.

1333
00:43:57,061 --> 00:43:58,381
We're actually divided by height.

1334
00:43:58,661 --> 00:43:59,761
- Oh, that's right.
- Yes.

1335
00:43:59,861 --> 00:44:01,960
I have to admit, they won't be easy to beat.

1336
00:44:01,961 --> 00:44:04,101
They give off major cheater vibes.

1337
00:44:05,271 --> 00:44:07,100
(Had they turned to a life of crime, they would've caused major trouble.)

1338
00:44:07,101 --> 00:44:08,570
- We're at an advantage.
- It's not bad.

1339
00:44:08,571 --> 00:44:09,741
Right. We're at an advantage.

1340
00:44:10,301 --> 00:44:12,541
We have a shot at sleeping indoors.

1341
00:44:13,071 --> 00:44:14,080
You're always lucky.

1342
00:44:14,081 --> 00:44:15,640
- You're lucky with your teams.
- I always have the best team luck.

1343
00:44:15,641 --> 00:44:17,240
- Then that's all that matters.
- Yes, I'm lucky with my teams.

1344
00:44:17,241 --> 00:44:18,411
- We've got this.
- Right.

1345
00:44:18,611 --> 00:44:20,010
The first game you'll play is...

1346
00:44:20,011 --> 00:44:21,020
(They will begin the first game.)

1347
00:44:21,021 --> 00:44:22,821
Face Stamp Fencing.

1348
00:44:23,551 --> 00:44:25,021
We're at a massive disadvantage.

1349
00:44:25,491 --> 00:44:28,490
(How to play Face Stamp Fencing)

1350
00:44:28,491 --> 00:44:30,320
Every member of the teams will play...

1351
00:44:30,321 --> 00:44:31,590
a 1-on-1 match.

1352
00:44:31,591 --> 00:44:33,560
Players will wear ink-covered gloves...

1353
00:44:33,561 --> 00:44:35,800
and stamp the circles on their opponent's cheeks.

1354
00:44:35,801 --> 00:44:38,030
The first one to fill them in wins.

1355
00:44:38,031 --> 00:44:39,831
(The first one to fill both circles in wins!)

1356
00:44:39,971 --> 00:44:42,101
(Nobody wants to sleep outdoors in the pouring rain.)

1357
00:44:42,471 --> 00:44:45,311
I'll show you what I've got and make it up to you for picking me.

1358
00:44:45,641 --> 00:44:48,080
I can beat all three of them all by myself.

1359
00:44:48,081 --> 00:44:49,441
But I don't want them to pass out.

1360
00:44:50,441 --> 00:44:53,051
(The members of Team Tall have a physical advantage.)

1361
00:44:54,481 --> 00:44:55,981
For your information,

1362
00:44:56,121 --> 00:44:58,291
Yong Jin just said,

1363
00:44:58,721 --> 00:44:59,721
"I'm good at this."

1364
00:44:59,891 --> 00:45:01,160
I even beat Dong Hyun before.

1365
00:45:01,161 --> 00:45:02,221
- Really?
- Really?

1366
00:45:02,491 --> 00:45:04,090
You should look here, not the eyes.

1367
00:45:04,091 --> 00:45:05,260
(Team Short, with variety show aces, is expected to show unique skills.)

1368
00:45:05,261 --> 00:45:06,701
That helps you respond more quickly.

1369
00:45:07,291 --> 00:45:10,731
Team Tall and Team Short, are you all ready?

1370
00:45:10,871 --> 00:45:13,200
First players from each team, please step forward.

1371
00:45:13,201 --> 00:45:14,641
- Who is it?
- Step forward, please.

1372
00:45:14,971 --> 00:45:16,670
From Team Tall, the one with the heart of a warrior...

1373
00:45:16,671 --> 00:45:19,510
and the blood of a ninja, Lee Joon is up!

1374
00:45:19,511 --> 00:45:20,511
- What? Jong Min came out?
- You fight an idiot with an idiot.

1375
00:45:20,512 --> 00:45:21,710
Lee Joon is up!

1376
00:45:21,711 --> 00:45:22,940
(Jong Min will fight against Joon.)

1377
00:45:22,941 --> 00:45:25,150
Kim Jong Min!

1378
00:45:25,151 --> 00:45:26,281
Hey, you should win this.

1379
00:45:26,351 --> 00:45:27,981
- Let's go!
- The heart of a warrior.

1380
00:45:28,551 --> 00:45:29,551
Okay.

1381
00:45:30,721 --> 00:45:31,751
Oh, my gosh.

1382
00:45:32,091 --> 00:45:34,220
- My hand feels heavy.
- Slather it on both sides. Good.

1383
00:45:34,221 --> 00:45:36,237
(Both players are solemnly soaking their gloves in the ink.)

1384
00:45:36,261 --> 00:45:38,261
- Here comes the ninja!
- Hey, listen.

1385
00:45:38,491 --> 00:45:40,660
You just paint my face, not slap me, okay?

1386
00:45:40,661 --> 00:45:41,830
(Joon can't hear him.)

1387
00:45:41,831 --> 00:45:43,100
I don't want anyone to get hurt,

1388
00:45:43,101 --> 00:45:44,807
but if it means winning, I don't mind if you get hurt.

1389
00:45:44,831 --> 00:45:45,831
Hey.

1390
00:45:45,832 --> 00:45:47,200
- Show them what you've got.
- Show them what you've got.

1391
00:45:47,201 --> 00:45:48,770
Players, get ready.

1392
00:45:48,771 --> 00:45:49,771
(Face Stamp Fencing, Round 1, Joon versus Jong Min)

1393
00:45:49,772 --> 00:45:51,170
- You're a ninja!
- Look at his eyes.

1394
00:45:51,171 --> 00:45:53,171
Hey, calm down.

1395
00:45:53,371 --> 00:45:55,171
- Joon, don't get so worked up.
- Here we go.

1396
00:45:55,881 --> 00:45:56,881
(Joon versus Jong Min, the game begins!)

1397
00:45:56,882 --> 00:45:58,011
This is a fencing match.

1398
00:45:59,111 --> 00:46:00,850
We'll take care of these three.

1399
00:46:00,851 --> 00:46:03,020
(They're charging straight at each other.)

1400
00:46:03,021 --> 00:46:04,221
Jong Min, don't get timid.

1401
00:46:04,491 --> 00:46:05,790
Here I come! Take this!

1402
00:46:05,791 --> 00:46:06,927
(They're standing face to face.)

1403
00:46:06,951 --> 00:46:09,290
Wait. I think Joon is clenching his fist inside the glove.

1404
00:46:09,291 --> 00:46:10,291
Hey!

1405
00:46:10,292 --> 00:46:11,590
(To be continued)

1406
00:46:11,591 --> 00:46:13,261
(His glove seems unusually bulging.)

1407
00:46:13,631 --> 00:46:15,201
Oh, good. Go!

1408
00:46:16,531 --> 00:46:18,077
- Get him the moment he gets close.
- That's good.

1409
00:46:18,101 --> 00:46:19,747
- I taught him that.
- You attack, I attack.

1410
00:46:19,771 --> 00:46:22,800
- The ninth strongest celebrity.
- Hold on a second.

1411
00:46:22,801 --> 00:46:23,908
(His attempt to attack falls through helplessly.)

1412
00:46:23,915 --> 00:46:24,266
(The 9th strongest celebrity fighter won't miss this chance.)

1413
00:46:24,274 --> 00:46:26,173
- You rushed your attack.
- Great job.

1414
00:46:26,174 --> 00:46:27,444
- Go for it.
- You rushed it.

1415
00:46:27,774 --> 00:46:28,873
I'm not the man you know...

1416
00:46:28,874 --> 00:46:30,594
(Joon launches a counterattack right away.)

1417
00:46:30,798 --> 00:46:32,298
- Okay!
- Okay.

1418
00:46:32,568 --> 00:46:34,768
(But...)

1419
00:46:35,808 --> 00:46:37,578
(Joon got hit too!)

1420
00:46:38,678 --> 00:46:41,378
(Both players successfully attacked each other.)

1421
00:46:43,048 --> 00:46:44,578
- That's good.
- Hey.

1422
00:46:44,848 --> 00:46:46,917
(The impact is stronger than expected.)

1423
00:46:46,918 --> 00:46:48,987
Jong Min attacked him too.

1424
00:46:48,988 --> 00:46:50,018
- Okay.
- Hey.

1425
00:46:50,158 --> 00:46:51,318
You should hit and step back.

1426
00:46:51,988 --> 00:46:53,868
This reminds me of the movie "Nowhere to Hide."

1427
00:46:55,958 --> 00:46:57,557
- It seems difficult.
- Hit and step back.

1428
00:46:57,558 --> 00:46:58,927
(Enemies always cross paths...)

1429
00:46:58,928 --> 00:47:01,498
(on a narrow log bridge on a rainy day.)

1430
00:47:02,068 --> 00:47:03,597
- Close the distance.
- Bring it on.

1431
00:47:03,598 --> 00:47:05,397
(Just like a scene straight out of a noir film, )

1432
00:47:05,398 --> 00:47:06,807
(they both throw an ink punch at each other.)

1433
00:47:06,808 --> 00:47:08,144
- Be careful. You might get hurt.
- Just do as I told you.

1434
00:47:08,168 --> 00:47:09,907
- Duck inside and aim higher.
- Go.

1435
00:47:09,908 --> 00:47:11,077
Keep your hand behind your back.

1436
00:47:11,078 --> 00:47:13,077
(Which of them will survive this fight?)

1437
00:47:13,078 --> 00:47:14,078
- That's good.
- Keep your hand behind your back.

1438
00:47:14,079 --> 00:47:15,607
That's what I'm talking about! Okay!

1439
00:47:15,608 --> 00:47:17,778
(Jong Min got hit first again.)

1440
00:47:18,548 --> 00:47:19,717
Okay. You did well.

1441
00:47:19,718 --> 00:47:21,748
(The former ninja's ruthless attack)

1442
00:47:22,048 --> 00:47:23,718
(Jong Min's point of view)

1443
00:47:24,558 --> 00:47:27,188
(Joon even casually looks back to see if it's over.)

1444
00:47:27,488 --> 00:47:29,397
- There's still some blank space.
- It's not over yet.

1445
00:47:29,398 --> 00:47:30,957
It's not over. There's some blank space at the bottom.

1446
00:47:30,958 --> 00:47:32,027
Everything went black.

1447
00:47:32,028 --> 00:47:33,467
(There's a tiny bit of blank space left.)

1448
00:47:33,468 --> 00:47:34,948
Is it okay to air his face like that?

1449
00:47:35,768 --> 00:47:36,798
Is it okay?

1450
00:47:37,038 --> 00:47:39,538
He looks like a bleeding UFC fighter. Is it okay?

1451
00:47:39,638 --> 00:47:41,167
You can turn the tables. You have only one shot.

1452
00:47:41,168 --> 00:47:42,207
This is really difficult.

1453
00:47:42,208 --> 00:47:44,878
You brat! I won't go easy on you! You punk!

1454
00:47:45,578 --> 00:47:46,578
(Jong Min still has a chance to win.)

1455
00:47:46,579 --> 00:47:47,777
- Close the distance more.
- Come on!

1456
00:47:47,778 --> 00:47:48,907
Jong Min, you'll lose at this rate.

1457
00:47:48,908 --> 00:47:49,978
You can get in there.

1458
00:47:50,578 --> 00:47:51,647
That's good!

1459
00:47:51,648 --> 00:47:54,548
(Now, there really is "nowhere to hide.")

1460
00:47:56,018 --> 00:47:58,918
(They're trading punches.)

1461
00:48:00,428 --> 00:48:02,597
(Joon unleashes an advanced technique.)

1462
00:48:02,598 --> 00:48:04,158
Wait, hold on. Oh, gosh.

1463
00:48:04,998 --> 00:48:05,998
That's good!

1464
00:48:06,398 --> 00:48:08,567
- Hurry up and step back now.
- Why?

1465
00:48:08,568 --> 00:48:10,438
(The game is over.)

1466
00:48:10,568 --> 00:48:11,638
You did your best.

1467
00:48:16,178 --> 00:48:18,277
Joon won the first round.

1468
00:48:18,278 --> 00:48:19,918
(Face Stamp Fencing, Round 1, Joon wins.)

1469
00:48:20,408 --> 00:48:23,018
- Give me some water.
- Great job.

1470
00:48:23,248 --> 00:48:25,477
Give me some water. I'll pour it over Jong Min's face.

1471
00:48:25,478 --> 00:48:26,487
(His face is covered with ink.)

1472
00:48:26,488 --> 00:48:27,488
He did his best.

1473
00:48:28,118 --> 00:48:29,717
- It's more difficult than it seems.
- It seems difficult.

1474
00:48:29,718 --> 00:48:31,018
It requires stamina.

1475
00:48:32,058 --> 00:48:34,688
(Both the winner and the loser have ink all over their faces.)

1476
00:48:36,198 --> 00:48:37,527
- I'm okay.
- Let me have a look at you.

1477
00:48:37,528 --> 00:48:38,997
- Why don't you wash...
- No, I'm fine.

1478
00:48:38,998 --> 00:48:40,367
(Rain, sweat, and ink)

1479
00:48:40,368 --> 00:48:41,474
Let's continue the momentum.

1480
00:48:41,498 --> 00:48:43,798
Second players from each team, please step forward.

1481
00:48:44,498 --> 00:48:45,638
The giant of 2 Days 1 Night.

1482
00:48:46,968 --> 00:48:48,068
Lee Ki Taek!

1483
00:48:48,368 --> 00:48:50,237
Lee Yong Jin with an undefeated record!

1484
00:48:50,238 --> 00:48:51,937
- Lee Yong Jin! Yes!
- This is...

1485
00:48:51,938 --> 00:48:54,108
- It's a match between the newbies.
- That's right.

1486
00:48:54,978 --> 00:48:57,024
- Stretch your arm and you'll win.
- Just stretch my arm?

1487
00:48:57,048 --> 00:48:59,287
I've never lost in this game. I've played it only once, though.

1488
00:48:59,288 --> 00:49:01,287
We'll begin now. Get ready!

1489
00:49:01,288 --> 00:49:02,734
(Who will be the winner of the match between the newbies?)

1490
00:49:02,758 --> 00:49:04,087
We'll begin Round Two.

1491
00:49:04,088 --> 00:49:05,488
(I can't be the losing card again.)

1492
00:49:06,458 --> 00:49:08,788
(He tries to intimidate his opponent with a shout.)

1493
00:49:09,498 --> 00:49:11,634
(Face Stamp Fencing, Round 2, Ki Taek versus Yong Jin)

1494
00:49:11,658 --> 00:49:13,428
(Striding)

1495
00:49:13,868 --> 00:49:16,237
(Kangaroo Taek is charging forward with his long legs.)

1496
00:49:16,238 --> 00:49:17,497
He has the heart of a warrior.

1497
00:49:17,498 --> 00:49:18,844
- They're touching gloves.
- That's good.

1498
00:49:18,868 --> 00:49:20,908
Show us why you joined 2 Days 1 Night!

1499
00:49:21,108 --> 00:49:22,138
Ki Taek, you've got this.

1500
00:49:22,708 --> 00:49:24,708
- Ki Taek, I like your stare.
- Bait an attack!

1501
00:49:24,938 --> 00:49:26,538
Make sure to keep that exact same stare.

1502
00:49:26,808 --> 00:49:27,808
Ki Taek.

1503
00:49:27,809 --> 00:49:29,048
- What?
- Oh, my.

1504
00:49:29,978 --> 00:49:31,978
(Yong Jin strikes first.)

1505
00:49:32,648 --> 00:49:34,587
(But Ki Taek casually dodges it with ease.)

1506
00:49:34,588 --> 00:49:36,487
He does have a long reach.

1507
00:49:36,488 --> 00:49:37,517
I have a long reach too.

1508
00:49:37,518 --> 00:49:39,557
(There is a distinct difference in their arm lengths.)

1509
00:49:39,558 --> 00:49:41,038
That's good. You have a longer reach.

1510
00:49:41,288 --> 00:49:42,527
(After dodging his attack quickly...)

1511
00:49:42,528 --> 00:49:43,627
He leaned back to dodge it.

1512
00:49:43,628 --> 00:49:45,428
(And then he counterattacks.)

1513
00:49:45,998 --> 00:49:48,128
(They attacked each other at the same time again!)

1514
00:49:56,038 --> 00:49:57,708
- Hey, step back.
- Oh, no, Yong Jin.

1515
00:49:58,178 --> 00:50:00,147
- Gosh. If he gets hit again...
- Step back.

1516
00:50:00,148 --> 00:50:01,577
Look at Yong Jin's eyes. He's intimidated.

1517
00:50:01,578 --> 00:50:02,578
I can just tell.

1518
00:50:03,748 --> 00:50:06,218
(It's weird. I'm good at this game.)

1519
00:50:06,388 --> 00:50:08,247
- He's definitely intimidated.
- Yong Jin.

1520
00:50:08,248 --> 00:50:10,568
- I've never seen him like that.
- He lost his confidence.

1521
00:50:11,088 --> 00:50:12,187
(Yong Jin's point of view)

1522
00:50:12,188 --> 00:50:14,387
(I think a kangaroo punched me earlier.)

1523
00:50:14,388 --> 00:50:15,788
- Can I say a word?
- Sure.

