01:08:50,908 --> 01:08:52,878
(Somehow, it feels satisfying.)

2038
01:08:53,078 --> 01:08:54,448
You lost, right?

2039
01:08:54,848 --> 01:08:56,417
- You lost. You said something.
- You said something.

2040
01:08:56,418 --> 01:08:58,248
- He's totally weak.
- You said something.

2041
01:08:58,448 --> 01:08:59,488
You lost.

2042
01:08:59,718 --> 01:09:01,318
I hit his forehead.

2043
01:09:01,518 --> 01:09:02,888
Was that too pathetic?

2044
01:09:03,758 --> 01:09:05,017
You screamed.

2045
01:09:05,018 --> 01:09:06,528
You screamed. You couldn't win.

2046
01:09:06,628 --> 01:09:08,287
Yong Jin gets the first win.

2047
01:09:08,288 --> 01:09:10,004
Let's have another player. Hee Sung can come.

2048
01:09:10,028 --> 01:09:11,597
- You can go, Ki Taek.
- Okay.

2049
01:09:11,598 --> 01:09:13,298
I really endured the pain.

2050
01:09:13,428 --> 01:09:14,897
- You should attack first.
- I did my best.

2051
01:09:14,898 --> 01:09:15,967
- You're attacking first. Win this.
- Finish it.

2052
01:09:15,968 --> 01:09:17,338
Make him cry as well.

2053
01:09:17,468 --> 01:09:18,598
Make him cry.

2054
01:09:19,038 --> 01:09:20,307
His forehead is perfect for hitting.

2055
01:09:20,308 --> 01:09:21,567
It's nice.

2056
01:09:21,568 --> 01:09:22,637
(He's in serious mode after seeing the senior producer lose.)

2057
01:09:22,638 --> 01:09:23,638
Finish him!

2058
01:09:24,138 --> 01:09:25,177
It'll be hard to hit.

2059
01:09:25,178 --> 01:09:26,458
You should keep that expression.

2060
01:09:27,078 --> 01:09:28,158
(Sighing in disappointment)

2061
01:09:28,548 --> 01:09:29,647
(No damage done.)

2062
01:09:29,648 --> 01:09:30,777
That was hard.

2063
01:09:30,778 --> 01:09:32,017
What are you doing?

2064
01:09:32,018 --> 01:09:33,117
This spoon is weak.

2065
01:09:33,118 --> 01:09:34,717
Step back. I'll do it.

2066
01:09:34,718 --> 01:09:35,818
With this.

2067
01:09:36,818 --> 01:09:37,988
That won't work.

2068
01:09:38,518 --> 01:09:39,887
(Director Hee Sung attacks next.)

2069
01:09:39,888 --> 01:09:40,888
Okay.

2070
01:09:41,658 --> 01:09:43,097
Ki Taek won't be able to film dramas...

2071
01:09:43,098 --> 01:09:44,928
if he gets a scar on his face.

2072
01:09:45,328 --> 01:09:46,648
Don't you have to film something?

2073
01:09:47,198 --> 01:09:48,228
I do.

2074
01:09:50,438 --> 01:09:52,368
They're about the same level. We don't know yet.

2075
01:09:52,538 --> 01:09:54,468
- They're both not good at this.
- It felt fine.

2076
01:09:55,838 --> 01:09:57,607
Try practicing it somewhere.

2077
01:09:57,608 --> 01:09:59,208
Hit here.

2078
01:09:59,908 --> 01:10:01,478
Good.

2079
01:10:01,778 --> 01:10:03,647
- But...
- You should go all the way.

2080
01:10:03,648 --> 01:10:05,377
Go all the way. You shouldn't stop.

2081
01:10:05,378 --> 01:10:07,088
You should just hit.

2082
01:10:07,488 --> 01:10:08,888
Push through!

2083
01:10:08,918 --> 01:10:09,918
(Exclaiming)

2084
01:10:09,919 --> 01:10:10,988
Push through!

2085
01:10:11,918 --> 01:10:14,128
(He lost because he made a sound.)

2086
01:10:14,328 --> 01:10:15,328
(Laughing)

2087
01:10:15,329 --> 01:10:17,528
- What was that?
- Well done. You hit well.

2088
01:10:17,628 --> 01:10:19,508
- Well done!
- It's over, right? We won, right?

2089
01:10:19,628 --> 01:10:21,668
- We won, right?
- It's over. We won, right?

2090
01:10:22,168 --> 01:10:23,367
Okay.

2091
01:10:23,368 --> 01:10:24,968
- Okay.
- Why were you eating in secret?

2092
01:10:25,338 --> 01:10:27,607
The production crew was going to eat after everything.

2093
01:10:27,608 --> 01:10:28,707
Take a seat, Joon.

2094
01:10:28,708 --> 01:10:31,238
Yeong Kwang is amazing at grilling meat.

2095
01:10:31,378 --> 01:10:32,648
It's so good.

2096
01:10:32,948 --> 01:10:34,548
I need a plate.

2097
01:10:34,908 --> 01:10:36,317
There should be a few packs of ramyeon.

2098
01:10:36,318 --> 01:10:38,377
There are many.

2099
01:10:38,378 --> 01:10:40,388
- It's really good, isn't it?
- It's really good.

2100
01:10:41,188 --> 01:10:42,388
It's amazing.

2101
01:10:43,318 --> 01:10:45,057
Come and eat here, Jong Min.

2102
01:10:45,058 --> 01:10:46,087
(It tastes even better after all the hard work.)

2103
01:10:46,088 --> 01:10:48,027
- It's really good!
- Is it good?

2104
01:10:48,028 --> 01:10:49,908
It's really good. You grilled the meat so well.

2105
01:10:50,428 --> 01:10:51,657
(He now goes for the ramyeon.)

2106
01:10:51,658 --> 01:10:53,728
You can tell when you grill it like that.

2107
01:10:53,968 --> 01:10:54,998
This is nice.

2108
01:10:55,628 --> 01:10:56,897
It's really delicious.

2109
01:10:56,898 --> 01:10:58,998
- Do you have...
- This is a team dinner.

2110
01:10:59,508 --> 01:11:01,268
- This is really good.
- Give me your plate.

2111
01:11:01,538 --> 01:11:04,308
This is our third shoot. Are you feeling comfortable now?

2112
01:11:04,778 --> 01:11:07,178
I'm feeling more comfortable...

2113
01:11:07,708 --> 01:11:10,047
with the members and the producers.

2114
01:11:10,048 --> 01:11:11,618
What I was really happy about today...

2115
01:11:12,478 --> 01:11:15,188
I hadn't really seen the real Ki Taek yet...

2116
01:11:15,888 --> 01:11:17,457
as well as Yong Jin.

2117
01:11:17,458 --> 01:11:19,564
I think their true self is coming out and that's nice.

2118
01:11:19,588 --> 01:11:21,087
That's right. Me too.

2119
01:11:21,088 --> 01:11:22,527
I saw unlimited potential in him.

2120
01:11:22,528 --> 01:11:24,158
- Right. It's good.
- In the games,

2121
01:11:24,698 --> 01:11:27,698
his eyes get filled with spite from time to time.

2122
01:11:27,928 --> 01:11:28,968
Nice.

2123
01:11:29,098 --> 01:11:31,667
Ki Taek feels like the perfect member.

2124
01:11:31,668 --> 01:11:34,138
- Do I have potential?
- You have a lot of potential.

2125
01:11:34,308 --> 01:11:36,008
Just be like how you are now.

2126
01:11:36,778 --> 01:11:38,637
There were two Dobermanns today.

2127
01:11:38,638 --> 01:11:39,678
(Thank you.)

2128
01:11:39,878 --> 01:11:41,248
Gosh, I'm full now.

2129
01:11:41,478 --> 01:11:43,848
- Gosh, it was really good.
- That was great.

2130
01:11:45,748 --> 01:11:47,148
Was the floor this comfortable?

2131
01:11:48,148 --> 01:11:50,758
Gosh, it's a historic day today.

2132
01:11:51,418 --> 01:11:53,527
It's my first time sleeping indoors.

2133
01:11:53,528 --> 01:11:55,264
(Yong Jin's 1st time sleeping indoors after 3 trips)

2134
01:11:55,288 --> 01:11:57,697
- You must feel strange.
- Right.

2135
01:11:57,698 --> 01:11:58,927
I feel so happy.

2136
01:11:58,928 --> 01:12:00,398
(True joy)

2137
01:12:00,798 --> 01:12:03,837
You've seen DinDin for a while.

2138
01:12:03,838 --> 01:12:05,668
- Right.
- DinDin said this to me.

2139
01:12:06,108 --> 01:12:09,478
"Yong Jin, I went easy on you at the last moment..."

2140
01:12:09,708 --> 01:12:12,008
"since you had a cold." Do you think he went easy on me?

2141
01:12:12,138 --> 01:12:13,547
- He didn't go easy on you.
- Right?

2142
01:12:13,548 --> 01:12:15,307
- He did his best.
- Right, Se Yoon?

2143
01:12:15,308 --> 01:12:16,477
DinDin did his best, right?

2144
01:12:16,478 --> 01:12:17,977
He definitely did his best.

2145
01:12:17,978 --> 01:12:19,148
(He gave it his all.)

2146
01:12:19,318 --> 01:12:20,758
He seems to be keeping you in check.

2147
01:12:21,218 --> 01:12:22,248
- Me?
- Yes.

2148
01:12:23,018 --> 01:12:24,158
He...

2149
01:12:24,618 --> 01:12:26,858
saw me have no money in my wallet.

2150
01:12:28,628 --> 01:12:30,697
He doesn't think I'm rich.

2151
01:12:30,698 --> 01:12:32,457
Well,

2152
01:12:32,458 --> 01:12:35,468
you changed so much after just a week.

2153
01:12:35,998 --> 01:12:40,008
To be honest, I don't know what your true image is.

2154
01:12:40,138 --> 01:12:41,607
I don't know myself.

2155
01:12:41,608 --> 01:12:43,608
I'm going to visit a fortune-teller before I come.

2156
01:12:44,108 --> 01:12:45,677
I can tell what kind of person Ki Taek is.

2157
01:12:45,678 --> 01:12:47,947
Really?

2158
01:12:47,948 --> 01:12:49,918
(Positive Taek is completely transparent.)

2159
01:12:49,948 --> 01:12:52,017
(Current status: Happy)

2160
01:12:52,018 --> 01:12:53,617
- Gosh. This is great.
- Hold on.

2161
01:12:53,618 --> 01:12:55,587
It's also Ki Taek's first time sleeping indoors.

2162
01:12:55,588 --> 01:12:57,388
- Right.
- Gosh.

2163
01:12:57,488 --> 01:12:58,958
- You must feel strange.
- Right.

2164
01:12:59,558 --> 01:13:02,658
- It's nice, isn't it?
- Right. It feels great.

2165
01:13:03,528 --> 01:13:05,088
I enjoyed sleeping in the tent as well.

2166
01:13:05,298 --> 01:13:06,727
- But it's different, isn't it?
- But...

2167
01:13:06,728 --> 01:13:08,127
it can't compare to sleeping indoors.

2168
01:13:08,128 --> 01:13:09,228
Of course not.

2169
01:13:09,268 --> 01:13:11,497
Right. Having a bathroom next to you...

2170
01:13:11,498 --> 01:13:13,038
is a great sign of wealth.

2171
01:13:13,608 --> 01:13:14,667
Should I tell you something fascinating, Ki Taek?

2172
01:13:14,668 --> 01:13:15,738
Sure.

2173
01:13:15,868 --> 01:13:18,408
We'll reach our second month at the next shoot.

2174
01:13:19,238 --> 01:13:20,547
- Gosh.
- Already.

2175
01:13:20,548 --> 01:13:22,818
- Already?
- It's already our second month.

2176
01:13:22,918 --> 01:13:25,047
- Time really flies.
- Right.

2177
01:13:25,048 --> 01:13:26,368
(Two months went by really fast.)

2178
01:13:26,548 --> 01:13:29,458
You should perform during the Entertainment Awards.

2179
01:13:29,858 --> 01:13:31,118
The KBS Entertainment Awards?

2180
01:13:31,558 --> 01:13:32,657
What? Are you going to SBS?

2181
01:13:32,658 --> 01:13:34,128
- Oh, right.
- Where are you going?

2182
01:13:34,728 --> 01:13:36,298
Ki Taek will look great as the MC.

2183
01:13:36,598 --> 01:13:38,757
I think Ki Taek will do a great job.

2184
01:13:38,758 --> 01:13:42,268
I shouldn't ruin the Entertainment Awards.

2185
01:13:42,528 --> 01:13:44,298
Gosh.

2186
01:13:44,598 --> 01:13:45,797
You'll do great.

2187
01:13:45,798 --> 01:13:47,768
I'll do it with Joon. I'll be a passenger.

2188
01:13:47,838 --> 01:13:49,838
You're making me the MC all of a sudden? Thanks.

2189
01:13:50,108 --> 01:13:51,607
I'm lucky when it comes to teams.

2190
01:13:51,608 --> 01:13:54,508
(I'm in a great team with Joon.)

2191
01:13:56,118 --> 01:13:57,648
Congratulations on sleeping indoors.

2192
01:13:58,018 --> 01:13:59,447
- Thank you.
- Congratulations...

2193
01:13:59,448 --> 01:14:00,587
on your first time sleeping indoors.

2194
01:14:00,588 --> 01:14:02,218
I'm serious about this.

2195
01:14:02,488 --> 01:14:03,488
I'll be able to fall asleep in three minutes after hearing,

2196
01:14:03,489 --> 01:14:04,558
"Let's go to sleep."

2197
01:14:05,358 --> 01:14:06,928
Joon will know this.

2198
01:14:07,058 --> 01:14:08,657
I always give the others around five minutes.

2199
01:14:08,658 --> 01:14:10,728
You should fall asleep quickly.

2200
01:14:10,758 --> 01:14:12,227
Yong Jin said he fell asleep quickly.

2201
01:14:12,228 --> 01:14:13,698
Right. I fall asleep quickly.

2202
01:14:13,868 --> 01:14:16,467
I'll give you exactly six minutes, Ki Taek.

2203
01:14:16,468 --> 01:14:18,098
- Okay.
- Since you're new.

2204
01:14:18,168 --> 01:14:20,007
- He's being lenient.
- He has earplugs?

2205
01:14:20,008 --> 01:14:22,808
- Right.
- I'm sure you'll wake up from it.

2206
01:14:23,008 --> 01:14:24,008
- Really?
- Yes.

2207
01:14:24,009 --> 01:14:25,754
I never stayed in the same room with Se Yoon before.

2208
01:14:25,778 --> 01:14:27,848
- Can I get some earplugs as well?
- Right.

2209
01:14:27,908 --> 01:14:30,277
- I have to turn on the lights.
- I'll get the flashlight for you.

2210
01:14:30,278 --> 01:14:32,677
You're saying something different now.

2211
01:14:32,678 --> 01:14:34,687
Well, Joon warned me...

2212
01:14:34,688 --> 01:14:36,918
after experiencing you.

2213
01:14:36,958 --> 01:14:40,388
I'm the closest to you, Se Yoon.

2214
01:14:41,658 --> 01:14:43,558
I might hug you in my sleep. Be careful.

2215
01:14:44,598 --> 01:14:46,198
I might think you're my son.

2216
01:14:47,628 --> 01:14:49,567
- Good night.
- Good night.

2217
01:14:49,568 --> 01:14:50,698
It was a great day.

2218
01:14:50,768 --> 01:14:51,868
Good night.

2219
01:14:52,738 --> 01:14:54,068
Sleeping indoors feels great.

2220
01:14:54,568 --> 01:14:58,007
(Around 6 minutes and 30 seconds later)

2221
01:14:58,008 --> 01:15:00,908
(Let's block my ears.)

2222
01:15:01,208 --> 01:15:02,247
(Ki Taek is fast asleep next to him.)

2223
01:15:02,248 --> 01:15:03,748
(Thank you, earplugs.)

2224
01:15:04,118 --> 01:15:06,418
(Meanwhile, rain continues to pour in the field.)

2225
01:15:06,688 --> 01:15:09,458
(A lot of water has pooled.)

2226
01:15:09,658 --> 01:15:11,057
(The camera that was filming the tent...)

2227
01:15:11,058 --> 01:15:12,988
(gets flooded by the heavy rain.)

2228
01:15:13,828 --> 01:15:16,628
(DinDin came to check the sleeping area.)

2229
01:15:16,698 --> 01:15:17,998
This is bad, Jong Min.

2230
01:15:18,258 --> 01:15:19,528
- What?
- This is bad.

2231
01:15:20,028 --> 01:15:22,098
It's raining like crazy all of a sudden.

2232
01:15:22,168 --> 01:15:24,468
- It feels like a swamp.
- It feels like a swamp.

2233
01:15:25,298 --> 01:15:26,768
What do we do?

2234
01:15:27,568 --> 01:15:28,568
Look at this.

2235
01:15:29,578 --> 01:15:31,208
I thought it was sand falling.

2236
01:15:31,608 --> 01:15:32,878
This won't work.

2237
01:15:33,508 --> 01:15:35,948
(They decide to make an urgent move out of humane treatment.)

2238
01:15:36,078 --> 01:15:37,778
It would be great to sleep indoors, right?

2239
01:15:39,018 --> 01:15:41,648
We can't lose our real variety show mentality.

2240
01:15:42,018 --> 01:15:45,588
(Barely moving the tent to a space not to get rained on)

2241
01:15:45,618 --> 01:15:47,158
(Working hard)

2242
01:15:48,058 --> 01:15:51,028
(The rain on the blanket gets shaken off well as well.)

2243
01:15:51,598 --> 01:15:55,028
(Director Joo's disinfection service)

2244
01:15:55,328 --> 01:15:57,497
(The tent door gets sealed.)

2245
01:15:57,498 --> 01:15:59,068
- Okay.
- Okay!

2246
01:15:59,738 --> 01:16:01,967
We'll sleep with this open when the lights go off.

2247
01:16:01,968 --> 01:16:03,008
Okay!

2248
01:16:03,978 --> 01:16:05,108
Thank you.

2249
01:16:06,278 --> 01:16:08,207
Have a good night.

2250
01:16:08,208 --> 01:16:09,408
(Have a good night.)

2251
01:16:09,648 --> 01:16:11,918
(The busy day finally comes to an end!)

2252
01:16:12,418 --> 01:16:17,288
(A quiet morning comes to Gyeongju while everyone is asleep.)

2253
01:16:17,758 --> 01:16:20,088
(The rain still hasn't stopped.)

2254
01:16:20,388 --> 01:16:22,928
(The yard is pooled with rain.)

2255
01:16:23,058 --> 01:16:25,828
(Quiet! Jong Min and DinDin are sleeping.)

2256
01:16:26,998 --> 01:16:29,128
(It's time to wake up.)

2257
01:16:32,068 --> 01:16:34,438
(Sleeping target acquired.)

2258
01:16:35,368 --> 01:16:37,478
(Am I dreaming?)

2259
01:16:39,408 --> 01:16:40,477
(A suffocating confrontation with the camera)

2260
01:16:40,478 --> 01:16:42,078
(Wake up.)

2261
01:16:42,918 --> 01:16:45,848
(He wakes up after an intense battle with the camera.)

2262
01:16:46,318 --> 01:16:48,948
(The second target is Ki Taek.)

2263
01:16:49,218 --> 01:16:51,318
(He's wearing earplugs.)

2264
01:16:52,058 --> 01:16:54,528
(He won't even budge.)

2265
01:16:54,658 --> 01:16:55,887
(They are more targets equipped with earplugs and sleep masks.)

2266
01:16:55,888 --> 01:16:57,258
(Joon and Yong Jin)

2267
01:16:57,628 --> 01:17:00,427
(The final move to wake them up, turning on the lights)

2268
01:17:00,428 --> 01:17:02,068
Wake up, everyone.

2269
01:17:02,568 --> 01:17:06,368
(Good morning, everyone!)

2270
01:17:06,508 --> 01:17:09,268
(The sun is up again.)

2271
01:17:09,638 --> 01:17:12,478
(They're all trying to understand what is going on.)

2272
01:17:13,708 --> 01:17:16,077
Let's all head out now.

2273
01:17:16,078 --> 01:17:17,177
- Okay.
- Okay.

2274
01:17:17,178 --> 01:17:19,148
(He's about to sink into his pillow.)

2275
01:17:19,648 --> 01:17:21,288
Can I put on some sunscreen?

2276
01:17:21,648 --> 01:17:22,958
When did you get up?

2277
01:17:23,288 --> 01:17:24,418
I just got up.

2278
01:17:25,358 --> 01:17:26,757
He looked great.

2279
01:17:26,758 --> 01:17:28,104
(He looks this great even after just waking up.)

2280
01:17:28,128 --> 01:17:30,858
(He still hasn't returned from dreamland.)

2281
01:17:30,898 --> 01:17:32,458
I want to remove my eye makeup.

2282
01:17:33,498 --> 01:17:35,127
- What was that?
- My eye makeup.

2283
01:17:35,128 --> 01:17:36,998
(Ink eye makeup)

2284
01:17:37,098 --> 01:17:39,297
Get ready and come out to the hallway.

2285
01:17:39,298 --> 01:17:40,337
Okay.

2286
01:17:40,338 --> 01:17:42,808
(They're next.)

2287
01:17:43,678 --> 01:17:45,838
(Staying still)

2288
01:17:46,478 --> 01:17:49,678
(He got knocked out after the sudden move.)

2289
01:17:50,518 --> 01:17:53,618
(Jong Min is knocked down as well.)

2290
01:17:54,288 --> 01:17:55,648
- Jong Min.
- Yes?

2291
01:17:59,688 --> 01:18:03,998
(Awake)

2292
01:18:04,158 --> 01:18:05,727
(It's already the morning.)

2293
01:18:05,728 --> 01:18:07,198
Gosh, it's raining a lot.

2294
01:18:07,868 --> 01:18:09,068
Gosh.

2295
01:18:09,228 --> 01:18:10,497
(Along with the sound of rain, )

2296
01:18:10,498 --> 01:18:11,998
(everyone is up.)

2297
01:18:12,268 --> 01:18:13,537
(Ki Taek came out first after putting the sunscreen.)

2298
01:18:13,538 --> 01:18:16,208
Did you move here because it rained so much?

2299
01:18:16,538 --> 01:18:17,737
It rained too much.

2300
01:18:17,738 --> 01:18:19,578
Really?

2301
01:18:20,208 --> 01:18:21,608
- While you were asleep?
- Yes.

2302
01:18:22,078 --> 01:18:23,148
How pitiful.

2303
01:18:24,548 --> 01:18:26,447
You all slept well, right?

2304
01:18:26,448 --> 01:18:27,487
- Yes.
- Yes.

2305
01:18:27,488 --> 01:18:30,157
Pick one of these.

2306
01:18:30,158 --> 01:18:31,558
Choose a hairband of your choice.

2307
01:18:32,788 --> 01:18:34,828
Is this a pig?

2308
01:18:35,428 --> 01:18:36,957
(A slightly uncomfortable choice)

2309
01:18:36,958 --> 01:18:38,598
- Gosh.
- All right, everyone.

2310
01:18:38,758 --> 01:18:41,567
Check the one wearing the same hairband as you.

2311
01:18:41,568 --> 01:18:43,538
- Gosh.
- It's Joon and Se Yoon.

2312
01:18:43,898 --> 01:18:45,837
(Monkey, DinDin and Yong Jin)

2313
01:18:45,838 --> 01:18:46,867
All right.

2314
01:18:46,868 --> 01:18:48,907
The ones wearing the same hairbands are in the same team.

2315
01:18:48,908 --> 01:18:49,938
Yes!

2316
01:18:50,108 --> 01:18:52,308
(The eldest and youngest are in the same team.)

2317
01:18:52,538 --> 01:18:55,307
I have good team luck.

2318
01:18:55,308 --> 01:18:56,878
- Really? I'll break the streak.
- Yes.

2319
01:18:58,578 --> 01:19:00,258
I'm in the same team with the weakest one.

2320
01:19:01,018 --> 01:19:02,088
"The weakest one?"

2321
01:19:02,848 --> 01:19:03,857
- Then...
- Let me wake up...

2322
01:19:03,858 --> 01:19:04,917
before beating me up.

2323
01:19:04,918 --> 01:19:06,294
(Let me wake up before beating me up.)

2324
01:19:06,318 --> 01:19:08,487
We'll move to the next place...

2325
01:19:08,488 --> 01:19:09,888
- for the morning mission.
- Right.

2326
01:19:10,098 --> 01:19:11,328
- Move?
- Yes.

2327
01:19:11,728 --> 01:19:12,828
We're going to move by car.

2328
01:19:13,568 --> 01:19:15,068
- Okay.
- Let's go.

2329
01:19:15,368 --> 01:19:17,497
(What will be the morning mission in the morning rain?)

2330
01:19:17,498 --> 01:19:18,698
Let's go.

2331
01:19:19,038 --> 01:19:20,338
Where are we going?

2332
01:19:21,538 --> 01:19:23,608
It feels ominous that we're...

2333
01:19:23,838 --> 01:19:25,008
wearing waterproof mics.

2334
01:19:25,208 --> 01:19:26,984
It was because the mics got wet in the rain yesterday.

2335
01:19:27,008 --> 01:19:28,008
- Is that so?
- I asked them.

2336
01:19:28,009 --> 01:19:29,407
- I see.
- They were still wet.

2337
01:19:29,408 --> 01:19:30,717
- Is that so?
- Yes.

2338
01:19:30,718 --> 01:19:32,398
Gosh. I thought there was something to it.

2339
01:19:32,518 --> 01:19:33,747
I feel relieved now.

2340
01:19:33,748 --> 01:19:35,088
- Right.
- Gosh.

2341
01:19:35,318 --> 01:19:37,588
Where could we be going with the bus?

2342
01:19:38,318 --> 01:19:40,558
I'm curious and worried at the same time.

2343
01:19:41,428 --> 01:19:43,548
Are we going for some tteokgalbi? Where are we going?

2344
01:19:43,828 --> 01:19:44,998
Ki Taek said he was hungry.

2345
01:19:45,328 --> 01:19:46,357
Really?

2346
01:19:46,358 --> 01:19:48,767
When I have something late at night before going to bed,

2347
01:19:48,768 --> 01:19:50,938
- Right.
- I feel hungry right away.

2348
01:19:51,268 --> 01:19:53,184
- I feel hungry right now.
- He really is a big eater.

2349
01:19:53,208 --> 01:19:55,068
He's a big eater.

2350
01:19:55,168 --> 01:19:56,608
He eats small portions often.

2351
01:19:56,938 --> 01:19:58,507
(After moving some more while dreaming of a good meal...)

2352
01:19:58,508 --> 01:19:59,808
We always have that regret.

2353
01:19:59,848 --> 01:20:02,208
(The sign for Bulguksa can be seen from afar.)

2354
01:20:02,508 --> 01:20:03,678
Isn't it Bulguksa?

2355
01:20:04,718 --> 01:20:06,948
Bulguksa can't be left out when it comes to Gyeongju.

2356
01:20:07,148 --> 01:20:08,288
That must be it.

2357
01:20:08,688 --> 01:20:09,718
Hold on!

2358
01:20:10,218 --> 01:20:11,658
Right now,

2359
01:20:12,188 --> 01:20:13,928
- we're wearing headbands.
- Right.

2360
01:20:14,288 --> 01:20:16,088
- Are we going to an amusement park?
- Right.

2361
01:20:16,128 --> 01:20:17,527
- That must be it.
- Right?

2362
01:20:17,528 --> 01:20:19,327
- That must be it.
- Are we going to see...

2363
01:20:19,328 --> 01:20:22,368
(A thrilling roller coaster appears right away.)

2364
01:20:22,898 --> 01:20:24,538
- That must be it.
- I can't get on that.

2365
01:20:24,668 --> 01:20:28,068
(Welcome to the amusement park.)

2366
01:20:28,538 --> 01:20:30,978
(What will be the morning mission in the amusement park?)

2367
01:20:31,008 --> 01:20:32,088
Do you like going on rides?

2368
01:20:32,338 --> 01:20:33,507
- I do.
- You do?

2369
01:20:33,508 --> 01:20:35,147
- Of course.
- DinDin enjoys rides as well.

2370
01:20:35,148 --> 01:20:36,377
- What about you?
- I do, too.

2371
01:20:36,378 --> 01:20:37,677
What about those who can't go on rides?

2372
01:20:37,678 --> 01:20:39,018
- We have an advantage.
- Right.

2373
01:20:39,218 --> 01:20:41,164
- You can't go on rides, Ki Taek?
- I'm afraid of them.

2374
01:20:41,188 --> 01:20:42,318
I see.

2375
01:20:42,418 --> 01:20:43,617
Why don't we pick teams again?

2376
01:20:43,618 --> 01:20:45,088
Jong Min can't go on rides at all.

2377
01:20:45,488 --> 01:20:47,634
- We should pick new teams.
- We should have at least one.

2378
01:20:47,658 --> 01:20:48,764
- I can't go on rides.
- Right.

2379
01:20:48,788 --> 01:20:51,028
- You and I can't go on rides.
- I wonder what it'll be.

2380
01:20:51,758 --> 01:20:52,997
We'll have to get on a ride.

2381
01:20:52,998 --> 01:20:55,928
(What is waiting for them?)

2382
01:20:56,768 --> 01:20:57,798
What is this?

2383
01:20:58,338 --> 01:20:59,338
It's scary.

2384
01:20:59,498 --> 01:21:00,737
- The log ride?
- That one.

2385
01:21:00,738 --> 01:21:02,538
Gosh, does it go straight down?

2386
01:21:03,878 --> 01:21:05,978
(They arrive at their destination.)

2387
01:21:07,448 --> 01:21:09,378
The log ride is high up.

2388
01:21:10,418 --> 01:21:11,647
It goes up a lot.

2389
01:21:11,648 --> 01:21:12,878
(Incredible speed)

2390
01:21:13,148 --> 01:21:15,187
- It won't be easy.
- What are we going to do?

2391
01:21:15,188 --> 01:21:18,388
(It looks intense.)

2392
01:21:18,888 --> 01:21:20,557
Gosh, the log ride is high up.

2393
01:21:20,558 --> 01:21:21,727
(They head to the ride with anxious thoughts.)

2394
01:21:21,728 --> 01:21:22,887
It's high up.

2395
01:21:22,888 --> 01:21:24,258
It's too high up.

2396
01:21:24,358 --> 01:21:27,197
(Right at the moment, a boat plunges from above to welcome them.)

2397
01:21:27,198 --> 01:21:28,198
What?

2398
01:21:28,199 --> 01:21:29,297
(And a refreshing splash of water pours down.)

2399
01:21:29,298 --> 01:21:30,438
What was that?

2400
01:21:31,398 --> 01:21:33,237
Gosh, it makes me want to pee. I'm so nervous.

2401
01:21:33,238 --> 01:21:34,907
(The scene makes them want to run to the restroom.)

2402
01:21:34,908 --> 01:21:36,607
So, we are at an amusement park now.

2403
01:21:36,608 --> 01:21:39,208
- Yes.
- Did you know that...

2404
01:21:39,638 --> 01:21:41,148
- Route Seven ends in Busan?
- Yes.

2405
01:21:41,308 --> 01:21:43,347
So we're planning to go all the way to the end.

2406
01:21:43,348 --> 01:21:44,478
We're really going to Busan.

2407
01:21:44,618 --> 01:21:46,724
- We're really going.
- I don't think all of us are going.

2408
01:21:46,748 --> 01:21:48,688
Actually, we did see this coming.

2409
01:21:48,748 --> 01:21:50,817
Now, we will be choosing two people.

2410
01:21:50,818 --> 01:21:52,688
- Two? One team?
- Yes.

2411
01:21:53,528 --> 01:21:54,928
I think I know who is going.

2412
01:21:55,188 --> 01:21:56,188
- You do?
- Yes.

2413
01:21:56,189 --> 01:21:57,398
I think I know who is going.

2414
01:21:58,728 --> 01:21:59,728
- You do?
- Yes.

2415
01:21:59,728 --> 01:22:00,728
Who's going?

2416
01:22:02,468 --> 01:22:03,497
I'm going.

2417
01:22:03,498 --> 01:22:05,214
(It's me, Kim Jong Min, the biggest coward.)

2418
01:22:05,238 --> 01:22:06,608
Have a nice trip, Jong Min.

2419
01:22:07,268 --> 01:22:08,368
We'll see you later.

2420
01:22:09,008 --> 01:22:10,408
- I think we'll be going.
- Right.

2421
01:22:11,138 --> 01:22:12,437
DinDin,

2422
01:22:12,438 --> 01:22:13,777
- we're on the same side, right?
- I think we'll be going.

2423
01:22:13,778 --> 01:22:14,878
Of course.

2424
01:22:14,948 --> 01:22:16,918
I'm just worried because of DinDin.

2425
01:22:17,518 --> 01:22:20,247
Actually, DinDin has a schedule in Busan today.

2426
01:22:20,248 --> 01:22:21,617
I'm going to sing at a wedding ceremony.

2427
01:22:21,618 --> 01:22:23,717
He's going to Busan anyway.

2428
01:22:23,718 --> 01:22:25,818
That's right. You should go then.

2429
01:22:26,088 --> 01:22:28,048
- Don't do anything silly, okay?
- You know what?

2430
01:22:28,488 --> 01:22:30,327
- I just want to lie down by myself.
- Okay.

2431
01:22:30,328 --> 01:22:32,804
Still, since you're going anyway, you should be the one to go.

2432
01:22:32,828 --> 01:22:34,597
- We don't...
- I don't know what we're playing,

2433
01:22:34,598 --> 01:22:37,237
- but DinDin will pull it off.
- We don't have a schedule in Busan.

2434
01:22:37,238 --> 01:22:39,798
All right. This is Getting-Off-Work Splash,

2435
01:22:40,408 --> 01:22:41,937
which will blow the heat away all at once.

2436
01:22:41,938 --> 01:22:43,067
Okay.

2437
01:22:43,068 --> 01:22:46,238
One from each team will get on the ride...

2438
01:22:46,408 --> 01:22:48,848
and try to catch the water with a cup in hand.

2439
01:22:49,048 --> 01:22:50,348
- Ki Taek.
- One from each team?

2440
01:22:50,578 --> 01:22:52,618
You can do it, right? You should collect the water.

2441
01:22:54,248 --> 01:22:56,488
And the other member will stand...

2442
01:22:56,658 --> 01:22:58,257
in the splash zone on the bridge.

2443
01:22:58,258 --> 01:23:01,387
They will get drenched there while collecting the water.

2444
01:23:01,388 --> 01:23:03,998
(The team that collects the most water combined wins.)

2445
01:23:04,698 --> 01:23:06,098
Do you want me to get drenched?

2446
01:23:06,598 --> 01:23:07,598
Let's do that.

2447
01:23:07,928 --> 01:23:09,027
You can choose what you want.

2448
01:23:09,028 --> 01:23:11,667
Will you get drenched or get on the ride?

2449
01:23:11,668 --> 01:23:12,837
- I hate them both.
- We should collect water like this?

2450
01:23:12,838 --> 01:23:14,238
- Okay.
- But I hate the ride more.

2451
01:23:14,668 --> 01:23:16,307
Okay. Then I'll collect water on the ride.

2452
01:23:16,308 --> 01:23:17,308
Okay.

2453
01:23:18,038 --> 01:23:20,348
(Staring and nodding)

2454
01:23:20,378 --> 01:23:22,407
What do you want? I don't know what you mean.

2455
01:23:22,408 --> 01:23:24,047
- Since you're big...
- You want me to get drenched?

2456
01:23:24,048 --> 01:23:26,578
Yes. That's better.

2457
01:23:26,948 --> 01:23:27,948
You get on the ride.

2458
01:23:28,548 --> 01:23:29,848
I'm sure I'm good at this.

2459
01:23:30,558 --> 01:23:32,318
I'll go on the ride.

2460
01:23:32,958 --> 01:23:34,557
- I'll try my best.
- Sure.

2461
01:23:34,558 --> 01:23:35,787
I don't really care whether I go to Busan or not.

2462
01:23:35,788 --> 01:23:37,397
Okay. I get it.

2463
01:23:37,398 --> 01:23:39,157
You've decided on your roles, right?

2464
01:23:39,158 --> 01:23:40,497
- Yes.
- All right then.

2465
01:23:40,498 --> 01:23:42,998
Please move to your spots now.

2466
01:23:43,338 --> 01:23:44,798
- Move!
- Move!

2467
01:23:45,168 --> 01:23:47,838
(Joon, Ki Taek, and Yong Jin are on the ride.)

2468
01:23:48,138 --> 01:23:51,708
Three, two, one,

2469
01:23:52,678 --> 01:23:53,707
zero.

2470
01:23:53,708 --> 01:23:55,048
(It takes off.)

2471
01:23:56,078 --> 01:23:57,948
I think DinDin is...

2472
01:23:58,948 --> 01:24:00,488
Gosh, this is scary.

2473
01:24:01,588 --> 01:24:02,618
(Screaming)

2474
01:24:02,988 --> 01:24:05,087
(Meanwhile, those who didn't get on the ride...)

2475
01:24:05,088 --> 01:24:06,828
- My goodness.
- Finish it in one go!

2476
01:24:07,958 --> 01:24:11,198
(They are waiting in the splash zone.)

2477
01:24:11,798 --> 01:24:14,098
I'll catch the water here and hit your cup to get yours.

2478
01:24:15,128 --> 01:24:17,397
Gosh, this is scary.

2479
01:24:17,398 --> 01:24:20,068
- I told you it would be high.
- Right. Gosh, what is this?

2480
01:24:20,238 --> 01:24:21,308
Gosh, this is...

2481
01:24:22,008 --> 01:24:24,878
- It's a lot higher than I thought.
- I know.

2482
01:24:25,838 --> 01:24:28,347
- Look at the angle of this drop.
- Let's go, guys.

2483
01:24:28,348 --> 01:24:30,247
- The angle.
- This doesn't make sense.

2484
01:24:30,248 --> 01:24:31,877
Let's go, guys!

2485
01:24:31,878 --> 01:24:33,617
- It's unbelievable, right?
- 2 Days 1 Night!

2486
01:24:33,618 --> 01:24:34,717
It's terrifying, isn't it?

2487
01:24:34,718 --> 01:24:36,118
This doesn't make sense.

2488
01:24:36,518 --> 01:24:38,417
- This is impossible.
- It's all right.

2489
01:24:38,418 --> 01:24:40,428
2 Days 1 Night!

2490
01:24:41,058 --> 01:24:42,688
I'm in big trouble.

2491
01:24:42,788 --> 01:24:43,928
Let's go.

2492
01:24:44,228 --> 01:24:45,827
Let's go.

2493
01:24:45,828 --> 01:24:47,344
(The boat has reached the top in the meantime.)

2494
01:24:47,368 --> 01:24:49,597
- Let's go.
- Look down there. It's so high.

2495
01:24:49,598 --> 01:24:51,038
The pain is temporary.

2496
01:24:51,198 --> 01:24:52,997
- Let's get over it.
- Let's get over it.

2497
01:24:52,998 --> 01:24:54,968
- Let's get over it.
- There we go!

2498
01:24:55,108 --> 01:24:56,937
There it is. Let's go!

2499
01:24:56,938 --> 01:24:57,978
(It's going down now.)

2500
01:24:58,108 --> 01:24:59,138
Let's go!

2501
01:24:59,438 --> 01:25:01,547
(If you can't avoid it, enjoy it.)

2502
01:25:01,548 --> 01:25:03,078
Let's go. Okay.

2503
01:25:04,418 --> 01:25:09,248
(Plunging straight down 32m)

2504
01:25:14,028 --> 01:25:17,658
(The ultimate water splash)

2505
01:25:17,728 --> 01:25:18,898
It's coming.

2506
01:25:19,728 --> 01:25:22,098
(Get ready.)

2507
01:25:24,838 --> 01:25:27,508
(A water bomb explodes right before their eyes.)

2508
01:25:27,738 --> 01:25:30,778
(How much water did they collect?)

2509
01:25:31,238 --> 01:25:33,648
- What? It's not much.
- It's too little.

2510
01:25:33,848 --> 01:25:34,977
It's not much.

2511
01:25:34,978 --> 01:25:36,177
(Running hurriedly)

2512
01:25:36,178 --> 01:25:38,347
What are you doing? Are we allowed to do this?

2513
01:25:38,348 --> 01:25:39,377
(Collecting water drops under the eaves)

2514
01:25:39,378 --> 01:25:40,448
Can we do this?

2515
01:25:42,988 --> 01:25:44,057
Is this okay?

2516
01:25:44,058 --> 01:25:45,794
(He's trying hard to collect it while saying that.)

2517
01:25:45,818 --> 01:25:47,258
I don't think this is acceptable.

2518
01:25:48,158 --> 01:25:49,187
Look at him.

2519
01:25:49,188 --> 01:25:51,228
This is part of the water splash anyway.

2520
01:25:51,998 --> 01:25:55,198
(It's okay as long as we collect more water.)

2521
01:25:55,428 --> 01:25:58,397
(Meanwhile, the members on the boat)

2522
01:25:58,398 --> 01:25:59,538
I'm in trouble.

2523
01:25:59,738 --> 01:26:00,807
I messed it up.

2524
01:26:00,808 --> 01:26:03,208
- It doesn't get into the water.
- The water doesn't get in.

2525
01:26:04,808 --> 01:26:05,977
(Things are pretty much the same on the boat.)

2526
01:26:05,978 --> 01:26:07,378
The water doesn't get into the cup.

2527
01:26:08,348 --> 01:26:09,508
- It's all similar.
- Look.

2528
01:26:09,948 --> 01:26:11,388
- Look at this.
- It's almost empty.

2529
01:26:11,578 --> 01:26:13,118
- My goodness.
- What did I do?

2530
01:26:13,948 --> 01:26:16,187
They should do well. We're all the same here.

2531
01:26:16,188 --> 01:26:18,457
- What we did is meaningless.
- There's no difference.

2532
01:26:18,458 --> 01:26:19,758
- No.
- It's all the same.

2533
01:26:20,018 --> 01:26:21,027
Okay.

2534
01:26:21,028 --> 01:26:22,127
(It depends on the non-riders.)

2535
01:26:22,128 --> 01:26:23,258
Can you believe this?

2536
01:26:24,098 --> 01:26:28,168
(Every single drop counts here.)

2537
01:26:28,428 --> 01:26:31,768
(Now they take extreme measures, the socks.)

2538
01:26:31,998 --> 01:26:33,068
This isn't much.

2539
01:26:33,098 --> 01:26:37,038
(Squeezing)

2540
01:26:37,578 --> 01:26:39,708
(An overwhelming lead)

2541
01:26:40,908 --> 01:26:42,177
Good.

2542
01:26:42,178 --> 01:26:43,677
